{"text": "GTFO is a game created by some ex-Payday & Payday 2 developers. The game is on the store page for almost a year yet still is in  , so you should keep that in mind. One controversial thought is the fact that news outlets were advertising this game as a Payday competitor which just isn't true in my opinion. The game was developed and published by  Release Date : 9th December 2019 (Early Access). Last known update:  Well I might be the odd one out, but in all honesty I do think that this type of combination will not work out. Just think of it, if they add normal matchmaking you will easily matchup with Unicellular organisms ( Organisms with only one cell ) which means that you are going to play with pretty below average humans destroying the gameplay for you, or they keep riding their current system which just will not get enough players and it will never become casual. As mentioned stealth is the main focus of the gameplay. You will live and die pressing your crouch button and holding your trusty melee weapon. Well in order to explain that small sentence I should first explain the enemies and the entire setting. Youâ€™re basically thrown into some underground warehouse that has been infested with â€œSleepersâ€ as the Voice actors call them when spotting one. Question is, what are â€œSleepersâ€? Those guys are basically sound sensitive enemies, they will not attack you if you are smart with your movement and noise production. Truth be told, you may ask, but how can I kill them if they react to sound? Simple, use your melee and with a well charged hit on the head you got yourself a dead Sleeper. Other than that it is pretty difficult, using any Gun or pistol will simply alert the horde and believe me these things are pretty strong so I suggest you take the quiet route. Most of the times you do have to unlock some doors which will then cause the alarm to go off, at that moment you will need to use your guns and find a solid standpoint, best decision would be to find a ladder in order to have the high ground. Other than that we do have an excellent stealth game, it even stays true to the stealth genre as you can get past some areas without killing any enemies. Granted, it is actually very weird to call the shooting mechanics of a shooter a secondary thing, yet here I am writing you about that!  Your stock-bone loadout consists of a primary weapon, the game allows you to select a gun that fits you the most, you get a special weapon as well, basically a high-powered small capacity one for a few instances within the game. Lastly you get your melee and your tool which gives you certain â€œabilitiesâ€ ranging from a bioscanner that allows you to monitor every living life-form close to you or a deployable automatic shotgun turret that will shoot down moving targets in its range. Firing your manual weapons is pretty straight forward, kill everything that tries to attack you, if everything is quiet use your melee in order to win. In this game it's all about timing. Recoil control is average as well, usually the recoil is just inconsistent, as a new player I suggest using the shotgun or the pistol as the rifle recoil or basically the recoil of every automatic gun is just terrible especially using the scopes. Other than that you do get an acceptable shooter that will do decent for now. Keep in mind GTFO captures perfectly the atmosphere with its dark environment, only thing you can see sometimes are the lightbulb reflections off your gun's metal housing and the glowing fangs of the sleepers, truly a treat to see. GTFO makes use of the Unity engine which at first was pretty unexpected to me.                      The game is an amazing performer after the current update, amazing job by the devs and the helpful community. GTFO is still an unproven EA game, but it shines where others donâ€™t with its unique gameplay and amazing sound as well as the creepy visuals. On the other hand the gameplay is an unproven combination in my opinion  and the non-usable Menu might create some inconsistencies.", "appid": "493520", "steamid": "profiles/76561198120469552", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "571", "votes_funny": "20", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1602590400.0}
