{"text": "There's an answer of great playing if you don't pretend your own mirror to the others. Well, the first sentence is about general behavior when playing. What about my overall recommendation of Left 4 Dead? Let's remind some convenient facts about the game: 1. Left 4 Dead and all its software was not created to judge players or annoy people by amoral playing. Although we have our own rules and expectations, we should not pretend bad or unpleasant habits, that may be gain from another players or from our personal skills. 2. Left 4 Dead is a co-op game and the players should help each other in their team, no matter the level they are. Feeling of completed competition or game is very appreciated and everybody can do. Realize its right intention and have a good experience of playing. 3. Left 4 Dead was a game made for everyone, so it means that even 18- people can buy it and play it. What I'm not satisfied with - almost every person under 18, or let me say - a child, doesn't know all the useful tactics or hasn't learned them yet. I recommend team-playing. 4. Left 4 Dead should be a competitive game, and it really is. Although, the players are not so competitive, or they don't think properly when playing. This is the main reason for mistakes and unpleasant fails. But to have a fun is also not so bad. 5. And the last important thing to write about is, my closest, making a progress in game by yourself. Well, having your achievements done day by day is good, but the biggest award is given by playing itself. As the days went on, I felt myself stronger and happier. Don't forget to enjoy your game, no matter what kind it is... Thank you for reading. Arne Gedeon", "appid": "500", "steamid": "profiles/76561198019367417", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "9", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1319457600.0}
