{"text": "Two hard as nuts platformers games in one package, AVGN Adventures 1 is much shorter and much more linear but when you delve into AVGN Adventures 2 you might be extremely overwhelmed at how much there is to do and how many/how long the levels are. If you're a fan of AVGN and/or platformers I recommend you pick this one up, two games in a $15 package is an absolute steal, the key differences with these opposed to the originals are that they completely touched up the graphics/engine for AVGN Adventures 1 is the same engine used in AVGN Adventures 2, they also added the NERD letters from AVGN Adventures 2 into one for some added content. The game itself has also received some balancing changes due to how frustrating the original games were before being remastered, but don't worry if you're a masochist who wants that feeling of the originals then there is the old school difficulty but if you just wanna playthrough the games without getting absolutely frustrated there is the normal difficulty. Overall the game is worth the price, its the original games with new bits and crisper graphics as far as i've seen a few of the bosses were also replaced i'll give this game a 9/10.", "appid": "1162960", "steamid": "profiles/76561198008562340", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1603972800.0}
