{"text": "This game was everything I was hoping for. Just unadulterated fun.  New interference can be overwhelming for ppl who don't play games a lot or just get overwhelmed easily, but that is about the only thing I can think of.  Music is great. Gameplay is fluid once you learn all the stuff you need to dispatch the citizens of hell. It throws everything it has at you then lets you breathe for awhile, while you search for the secrets and some lore documents. Just like in 2016.  To all those soy boys in the reviews, moaning about the game after playing for an hour or two.  1. You can turn off the tutorials and hints in the settings if they bother you that much.  2. There are enough ammo supplies for you to kill every demon and your chainsaw recovers an extra use after some cooldown. I play on Nightmare difficulty and I didn't get any problems with the ammo. So if you are having ammo problems, you either don't move around the combat zones to pick them up or you just plain old suck and can't aim.  There is also shards that let you increase your ammo capacity. if you are still going low on ammo, heck you can lower the difficulty. If you are still no enjoying it then there is a cheat code in game that lets you have unlimited ammo.  3. You only need to login once with Bethesda to play. Stop making a huge deal out of it. If being online is so traumatizing for you can just play the game without the internet.  4. You can skip any cutscenes that play. If you don't want no story or cutscene, nobody is forcing you sit down and watch them. It takes 1 sec to skip them.  Don't let negative reviews discourage you from trying this game. Check it out for yourself. You can always refund it, if you don't like it.", "appid": "782330", "steamid": "profiles/76561198277809095", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1584705600.0}
