{"text": "Having an elderly black man call you honey. 5/5 Well, as for the real review: my standards for VR gaming are high, but still I am absolutely impressed by the quality of this game! The way how interactive everything is, is very immersive! Valve clearly tested this game a lot, and watched how people react in VR, and then made all those things possible.  The amount of polish on everything is very satisfying. Puzzles and combat are pretty challenging. Level design is top notch. Love the animations and high quality models like we've never seen before!  This is somewhat a 'cinematic game' and so it is far more motions sickness friendly than Boneworks for example. I personally would like to sprint and jump around, but you cannot do that here. Another thing missing here, is melee combat.  Well, you can swing a headcrab with a heavy object, and it gets knocked down, but you cannot do any real damage. You rely on guns and bullet management so you can kill all the bad guys. In conclusion, the game is indeed a masterpiece. Everything is solid and polished, but it does leave some things to be desired. Melee combat, free roaming, grabbing, sprinting and jumping. HL: Alyx is like a very well designed and beautiful carnival tea cup ride. And Boneworks is that older, not so gorgeus, but far more crazy and sickness causing ride. Which I personally like, and would like Alyx to be more like that. Regardless, its a solid 9,5 / 10 from me.  Playing this on full Valve Index kit. Thank you Valve for giving this game for free.", "appid": "546560", "steamid": "profiles/76561198043804128", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "371", "votes_funny": "27", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1584964800.0}
