{"text": "3089 is an open world fps game with rpg elements, and... that's pretty much it. the gameplay is extremely simple, and has a very basic pattern: complete random quests for money and experience which is used to increase your stats, such as gun damage, health, defense, energy, carry weight, etc. and buy guns, armor, or tools or loot parts from enemies and crates to build your own, then travel farther from the center of the world and face tougher enemies, and repeat. it's not a very large game, but it's good for a short session when you're bored, and there are many different ways to play the game; put a scope on your rifle and snipe enemies from afar, be a sneaky boi with a sword, run and gun with a rapid fire pistol, even piloting the aircraft you find scattered around the world. for $7 I'd say it's worth it.", "appid": "263360", "steamid": "profiles/76561198076719358", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1571054400.0}
