{"text": "Its alpha.Its a bit barebones. The building part is mostly solid even in this stage.I d prefer if they make the power grid a bit more complex and some kind of fire system-management comparable to the power grid system.That is if they make fire an actual event in the game cause now its not. The Ui is some times annoying.A quickly accessible jump button should exist,possibly a battle stations too. Story is underwhelming to non existant.Faction interaction is limited to trade although i did not push my luck.I think those should be story driven.The only time i tried to interact with a faction is when they got got by the pirates and i tried to help em with no option available to transfer surviving members of their crew or rebuilding their ship.Other than pirates no shots were fired between any other. A bit about my play and what i wanted.As a build sim it works.I spent most time finding the sequence of building the ship and then kept on by me greed will to gather resources.After that blank.Combat is rudimentary.Pillage and salvaging becomes uninteresting.No special items.No crew member rpg elements.I got the same 4 guys doing all combat and there is no progression. The FTL feel is there but there is so much missing at this time and im guessing nobody knows what exactly this game will end up looking like.Stations mentioned not in.Building items are in but with no use.No gun variety.No combat variety.Minimum ship configurations for combat.Boarding is rng.Even combat is rng.If u got 4 guns and they got 4 guns either you shoot first if you re in the system already and they lose or you lose.Sometimes they just flee repeatedly and you ll have to hop around cutting little pieces of their health bar . What i d like to see.Some FTL variation in combat and   FTL you could go drones,missiles,boarding,lasers,flamers,bombs and any combination you d prefer.You could decide between defence and agility.Characters could acquire skills or specialize.And there was always the rng jump or the story jump.Maybe thats the way to implement some certainty and story into the game.I could go through the whole game prolly without even firing a shot. Some kind of character development and consequences from their relationships and conditions.U got one suicidal?No prob.Do two members have the worst relationship?No prob.Some more items to equip them or even better some special items allover to incentivize the next jump the next hunt the next battle.Credits are worthless and everybody at this stage sells high and buys low except from you.It needs more balance on the trade-mine-produce cycle to force decisions other than hoarding huge amounts of materials.I claimed and built the extra ships just to unload the cargo hold. Same vibe overall with another stuck in alpha favorite of mine,starsector.U get the rush to acquire all the resources ships etc but a moment came when u wanted a mission a story and there just isnt one,so the game dies.Even starsector have some other aspects that work at its current state,like building or grinding status with some factions to \"get that ship\",smuggling,combat with escalating fleets and almost a functioning trade-produce-economy that incorporated more complex concepts. What i liked.Building is solid as already mentioned.Salvaging is gratifying at first and even mid game.I sinked many hours as you can see but what i cannot see is relaunching it without some major additions. So,its alpha and i dont want to not recommend.Everybody should come with their eyes open and their expectation curtailed. FTL with far less complexity at first sight is way more replayable.Starsector stuck in alpha for a decade is way more fleshed out and even cheaper with no prospects tho.", "appid": "979110", "steamid": "profiles/76561198310936845", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1594209600.0}
