{"text": "First character died from freezing. Second character died from trying to kill a bear. Third character got mauled by bear, but not killed. Healed with medical supplies. Got through a blizzard and the night on e-stims and coffee and the occasional 1-2 hour fire behind a tree because of the wind. Still living as of writing, on day 28 of survival. 10/10 would drink the hot coffee again. Now, I really do like this game alot. However, it is still in early access, and requires a bit of work before completion, so don't be disappointed. Pros: - STEAM WORKSHOP. I can't wait for modders to dig in. - Utterly immersive. - Sometimes a little terrifying. - Some tough challenges if you've already played it 239390259033783 times and are getting bored. - They're developing a storymode! - You will, at some point, have a brush with death. At first you'll probably succumb to The Long  Dark, but as you play it more, you'll learn how to pull through and believe me, it is satisfying  when you survive a major setback. Con (more of a warning against hype/expectations): - It's in early access; don't expect it to be how you thought it would, and expect changes in gameplay as it develops. Some things have only been partially implemented, while some things need some work/balancing before the game is ready to roll (such as some of the crafting recipes and resources/tools at the time of writing). Don't expect the game to be totally like IRL survival. It's a fictional game, and still being developed at that; and as such the lore/story may change too. Games change plenty between the different versions. Think of early access as a chance for the devs to playtest as much as possible - some popular and highly acclaimed games/series such as the Half-Life series (as an example) went through some truly enormous changes to the mechanics and asethetics before becoming the games we know today. My last advice is to wait until it's in a sale, and then buy it if you're still interested (as I did). Or you could wait until it's full release (there's no set date for this however, and will probably increase in price upon full release) and buy it then if it seems good. If you do get it: May the best survivor- um - have this complimentary deer carcass. Oh, I forgot to mention: Playable if you're a vegatarian. Probably. Well. Sort of. You're certainly hardcore if you survive in this game without meat for long periods of time.", "appid": "305620", "steamid": "profiles/76561198003061532", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1467720000.0}
