{"text": "The following preparations are required before playing this game. In order to have a scary and terrifying adventure.  --- Night time --- comfortable rotating chair  --- Home alone --- Headphones on a loud enough volume for you to hear every single creepy sound  --- Full screen  --- Now I haven't actually tried this myself because well I know I wouldn't be able to cope (I am a puss* I know) BUT... To really play like a pro, play this game in a room filled with clowns, dolls, etc. Trust me... That would be some scary shi*.  --- And if you want it to the Maximum maybe get drunk or get high before playing (I have witnessed this happen :3 )  The following preparations are for those who are too afraid to play it like a pro. ^^ --- Daytime --- Diapers / Nappies  --- With a group of people --- Speakers  I Recommend this game for people who like a LOT of thrill, I do not however recommend it for old people, trust me... I know from experience with my Grandparents... (I didn't let them play it fyi)  Good luck! Just trying to help :)  ( Oh and first time I played this game I played it like a pro, I fell off my comfortable rotating chair, onto the floor and stayed there for about 2 minutes because the first jumpscare was too much for me to handle, I haven't gotten past the 2nd night yet... YET )", "appid": "332800", "steamid": "profiles/76561198069246436", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "190", "votes_funny": "14", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1418040000.0}
