{"text": "I've played through the entirety of this game on my friend's PS4 and on my brothers' PS4s on several occasions because I didn't have the console myself and didn't plan to get one either. When I got this game for PC however I expected there to be flaws with controls and such, but after playing through a couple of the chapters through the first gameplays for each characters; the controls are really comfortable to play with and I don't expect there to be much flaws. I partially expected the click and drag interaction to be tedious, but thankfully it ain't a moment where you have to launch your mouse through your entire house to get one interaction done. A friend of mine gifted this to me, and I'm thankful for it. And if you read this, I will enjoy every bit of it.", "appid": "1222140", "steamid": "profiles/76561198035217790", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1594468800.0}
