{"text": "Alright, well, as you already know, Remedy is forced to take down Alan Wake from Steam, Xbox Store, GOG and other digital platforms due to expiring music licenses. Some may say it's stupid and some may say it's understandable. Me personally, I think that there are just some situations in which renewing licenses and keeping that game \"alive\" just for the sake of I don't know what is really not worth it. Remedy also stated today, that they can't just remove the tracks from the game, reason was \"large variety of engineering, resources etc.\". Now, it's also been stated that they are looking to renew them, but they don't have timeframe, which in most of the cases means that no, they're not going to renew it.  Alan Wake is 7 years old, there's been just plenty and plenty and plenty of opportunities to get it almost for free (today is that day too). I believe lot of you will remember 2013 and awesome Humble Bundle where it was for 1 dollar. Also, who knows how many copies was sold this year, and for what price, and then there is that major question if it is really worth to take care of new licenses, if Alan Wake is still able to bring some income and revenue. Who knows right? Now, I don't really want this \"review\" to be review yet. Thing is that I did not complete the game in time of this writing yet, I was close to the end of the game but still, there is no way I want to provide any word look into the Alan Wake game yet. Once I finish the whole game, I will write review for it, and edit it under this first article. Reason is, that I want to have opportunity to have review of Alan Wake, here at Steam, in my profile, because once it is gone from Steam Store, you can't obviously review it. I made same mistake with Metro series. I do have a lot of personal stories with Alan Wake, which I keep for myself this time and lot of times, eras and dates are related to Alan Wake that also with the quality of the game itself makes it one of the best games I have ever played and it helped climb this game on the TOP10 of mine.  Also I do have near identical coat as the Alan is wearing during the game, it is basically same, I just don't have those elbow patches in black, but in grey color. Otherwise it is 100% identical and I feel so awesome when I'm wearing that :D I also want to say to those people who have the game, don't sleep on it.  Those people who don't own the game yet, Alan Wake is pretty much worth actual retail price and I'm not even joking. This game is really one of few that is definitely worth full retail price of 30 euros/dollars so today, when you'll have opportunity to grab it in 90% discount for 3/4 dollars, holy sh*t go for it without thinking. That'll be one of the best buys you've done for the past couple of months. Last thing, that is on my mind, is big shoutout to Remedy. In this case, that they did notice us, that game is going to be removed, not like others who just simple don't give a flying f*ck and remove it without even saying words. So, thanks for that and for the headsup.  Also note that American Nightmare will not be removed from Steam.", "appid": "108710", "steamid": "profiles/76561198078193056", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "357", "votes_funny": "27", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1494676800.0}
