{"text": "I now know all the hype around Castlevania and the whole metroidvania genre... this game inspired me to play more of its genre. I love how it feels to hit an enemy once with a simple sword and see the little damage number going up. It's very addicting and reminds me of my childhood games. It's a quick pleasure. The game does get more complicated than simple 1-hit sword slashes, but you get the idea. The art uses colors like red, purple, magenta and cyan because it's about magic infused crystals (this magic happens to be demonic). I thought it was medium-hard. I 100%'d it by myself, but had to Google ONE part of the main story that I was just painfully stuck in. Had I the necessary patience (life is kinda in shambles right now), I'd be able to solve it, but I couldn't resist the temptation to look it up and did eventually. Anyway, it wasn't worth it in the end, I'd prefer having solved it myself. People that played can probably guess which part I'm referring to. The village (safe zone) could be bigger, have more NPCs, interesting quests and things to interact with, but the game makes up to this by having a lot of detail everywhere else and the focus is on the castle anyway. There's a lot to explore. It's a QUALITY game. If you like the genre, there's not much to think about.", "appid": "692850", "steamid": "profiles/76561198009906325", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1600344000.0}
{"text": "9.5/10 This game should've been a patch to the original but I got the game for only $20 from a friend and I am not dissapointed. This game has great visuals and the classic boss fights that started the series. Since I never played Prepare To Die edition, I chose this over the original since you know this natively supports 60FPS which you had to get DSFix on the original. I didn't want to get the hassle by downloading that so I instead got this and I've been pleased about this remaster. I look forward in playing more souls games and more fromsoft games as so far this has been a masterpiece of a game in my opinion even though it has a bunch of negative reviews because people are complaining that this game is more of a $40 patch than an actual game. If you never played dark souls and you would like to get started, I highly recommend playing this version of the game since it's actually polished and it has an alive community still if you would like to invade people or coop with others.", "appid": "570940", "steamid": "profiles/76561198043411658", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1537531200.0}
