{"text": "**Please Note Game Not Available on Steam Anymore** This was an amazing title back in its day.  I remember cruising around Hawaii in my 1984 Ferrari 308 GTS, ah the nostalgia. It featured two huge, beautiful open world maps, Ibiza and Hawaii, that you could cruise around and explore alone or with friends. The driving mechanics, car models, engine sounds and graphics were pretty solid for its day, not to mention it had an amazing soundtrack. Visit towns to customize and buy new Vehicles, Clothing, Hair styles and even Real Estate to store all your toys! It had pretty decent customization for cars, player avatars and even the interiors for the properties you bought. When visiting any shop or personal house, you would switch to first person and you had the freedom to explore and interact with the things around you. You could even see other real players while shopping around and you could even invite friends to visit your virtual home. This was something which hadn't really been done in a racing game before. It had many of the customization elements that even Grand Theft Auto 5 has now. Atari doesn't seem like they are doing all that much to keep their servers up and running these days so unfortunately the online aspect seems to be deteriorating slowly.  You can still play single player mode which is pretty fun but the multiplayer was where TDU2 shines. Test Drive Unlimited 2 will always be remembered as the game who truly broke boundaries and exceeded expectations.", "appid": "9930", "steamid": "profiles/76561197993310177", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "49", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1501243200.0}
