{"text": "On my first launch on the game I simply stayed in awe for a good amount of time at the life-like details in cutscenes and not just that, the game doesn't downgrade that at all while you're actually playing as previous two Yakuza remakes. There's more than few improvements that Dragon Engine brings to the table some of them increasing immersion by significant amount; biggest change in my opinion adds a smooth transition entering and exiting all the buildings removing the loading screens, combat and experience gaining had a complete rework. There's more of a reason to visit different eateries each having combos that award you with specific experience points. The four fighting stances have been combined into one which seems to have earned mixed opinions from the fans personally I like what they've achieved with a single stance although I missed some of the skills which were left out. Can't say much about the story you'll have to play it yourself to find out just that there's top notch writing as always, fleshed out new characters and I dare say Majima needed more content for the bonus chapters with him. That's more of a complaint not a negative from me, I loved the nicely done fan service. Mini games also have been completely reworked in a good way for me but doubt you'll hear that from everyone, the golf mini game was probably my favorite new one due to its harsh difficulty. - top notch voice acting - sound design & music - high quality plot  - free roaming immersion - new engine physics (combat ragdoll lots of fun) - more karaoke songs this time around - nothing worth mentioning A note for the translators:   is not part of english dictionary.", "appid": "927380", "steamid": "profiles/76561198048669872", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "24", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561809600.0}
