{"text": "I'm giving it a good review because of all the good memories i've made in this game in the past. When the original version of this game, \"War Z\" was released, it didn't take me long to rush to my wallet to see if I could afford it. The premise seemed unique, and well executed. The first couple hours of the game were harsh, but fun nontheless. Finding my first gun was such a remakrkable moment. I remember it up to this day, it was a normal handgun with 13 bullets in it ( I think a clock? ) in a gasstation. Same goes for my first death to a zombie, and player. The game was filled with life. ALmost every server was full and you had to look for low population servers to at least have a chance at surviving. I remember grinding all night and day with friends and then running all the way accross the map to bring our loot to the safezones so we would stack up a collection of weapons (Guns were super rare at the time). Later on after a couple of months of playing things changed. Encountering hackers was a daily thing, and without hacking yourself it was esentially unplayable. So all of us stopped playing. Weeks later the news dropped of the movie World War Z coming out. So all the sudden this game here was called infestation. Some more casual play later and boom. Me and 2 of my friends got banned from the game for no rreason at all. We had to rebuy the game for absolutely no reason. Months passed. Everyone i knew stopped playing, servers emptied out, and everyone just kind of forgot about this game. Here we are, years later.. I saw the game is free on steam so I gave it a download. And oh boy... what happened? Battle passes, competitive mode, skins, lootboxes (........) I mean COME ON!!! This game was the most unique, scary and intense survival horror open world experience i've EVER had. I came back to perhaps make more fun memories, to experience all the amazing new content.. but no. Now the loading screen is 200 ads for ingame content, the main menu a confusing mess, the UI and character screens just an counterintuitive mess, I played for about 30 minutes now, and I'm most certainly not coming back for a while. Thank you for making a game that impacted my childhood in an amazing way, and thank you for allowing me to make amazing memories. But the game right now is unplayable, unenjoyable, broken, empty, a mess. Get rid of all these stupid modes that work for other games.. This game was so unique.. you don't need this. Revamp the anti cheat system, don't ban for no reason and actually persue hackers. Change the weapon spawn rate.. why has every car 20 gusn on it wth? Well that was it. For now, Good bye, War Z / Infestation / The New Z Until our paths shall cross again :,)", "appid": "555570", "steamid": "profiles/76561198262641160", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1579176000.0}
