{"text": "Imagin if patrick stewart played han solo in star wars... well this game is nothing like that! Despite this, TSW is a really smart game, I had to learn latin, morse code, cryptic roman cyphers, musical notes and scales, binary code, advanced mathmatics, oh, and i ended up buying a book the game recommended!! Which helped me solve a puzzle! \"I â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ LOVE PUZZLES MAN!!\" After playing 200+ hours when describing this game I often refer to that movie inception. Have you seen that movie inception? Well, if you have; imagin that movie if decaprio had won an oscar! YEAH! INTESE RIGHT?! Now add Dr.Who and all his adventures with a dash of tactical situations imploring solid snake-like stealth and you got this game! Oh yeah, indiana jones is in this, there's also the lost arc, dracula, Rosamund Pike, and theres even a belmont achievment! The feeling you get after unearthing so many artifacts and solving so many mysteries is.. well take a moment to imagin the life of laura crofts sports bra... Yeah, feels that good! Plus all the tomb raiding!", "appid": "215280", "steamid": "profiles/76561198003960320", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "11", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1399032000.0}
