{"text": "I must say it's hard to drive without a wheel controller but you'll get countless hours of entertainment and relaxing by playing this trucking game. The physics are convincingly well simulated. You can put your favorite radio station or your own collection of music and drive. I also love every World of Trucks Challenge the developer regularly creates on special occasions (Christmas for instance). What is not good is the sounds of the horns. I've not yet found something that sounds like a real life wind horn, mods in this domain are either not compatible (obsolete) either very bad.", "appid": "227300", "steamid": "profiles/76561197976357676", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1547985600.0}
{"text": "This game is like a complicated relationship.  You're not sure if you should let go or if it's worth holding on, then they do something that makes you fall for them again. Then there's a lull in the relationship where you start thinking \"maybe I should move on\" but then they grab for your attention and email you and tell you how much they changed and you believe them. The next time you see them they just have new make up on and they look just as attractive as when you first met them. So you spend time with them hoping to rekindle that fire from the beginning and realize that you're not in love with them but you keep trying to make it work.  Y'all got friends together, what will they think? Your \"good\" friends are calling you stupid for staying. Your parents are yelling at you to stop typing to kill people.  Anyway, 368 hours later you realize that this is what love is. An unfinished story and a complicated gear grind that inexplicably pulls you back in at the mention of specialized gear.  Hey, 1.7 is coming out soon(er or later)! new stuff to do. kinda? Disclaimer: Not a solo kinda game. You can do the single player story alone but this game was made to be played with a group of friends. That's where your bread and butter is going to be replaying content with others. This is a cover shooter with heavy (stats) RPG elements and light social MMO elements.", "appid": "365590", "steamid": "profiles/76561198027474954", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1499428800.0}
