{"text": "I have many games in my library and not much time to play. So I tend to divide my time between games, only spending the most of it in the ones that, for some reason, grab my attention. This is one of these games for the following reasons:  1 - I can play it with my son (not as multplayer, but when it comes to decisons on what to do and where to go) 2 - It can be played in 30 min chunks without losing progress, making sure my kid goes to bed on time ;) 3 - The story is full of clichÃ©s, but its interesting, the characters are nice and funny (I especially like Sylvano!) and you never feel lost or without anything to do. 4- I really like the combat: its fun and varied. The monsters are normally very cute, which is funny and sometimes I even feel sorry to kill them! The AI that controls your characters in auto-fights is really good, reducing the grind of fighting lower level enemies and you can manually control them at the end of every turn if things turn out bad. 5 - The different cities / lands are varied and interesting, making every new place you go to a pleasant surprise. I haven't finish the game yet (~30h in), but I'm loving the journey and, for that, I highly  recommend it.", "appid": "742120", "steamid": "profiles/76561198030958664", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1543233600.0}
