{"text": "This controller will easily replace any that you previously had. Granted, it does take some getting used to. It may take you days, weeks or months to make sure it's comfortable in your hands. It's completely customizable and has hundreds of different combinations. The default themes aren't exactly the best so looking through the community ones is your best bet.  Big Picture mode needs some work and is frustrating if you're used to the normal mode. The controller is very frustrating at first, especially if you're playing an fps. However, I suggest you give it a try. Of course a keyboard and mouse is better but it's a close second.", "appid": "353370", "steamid": "profiles/76561198131449444", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1449748800.0}
{"text": "I strongly recommend this game. It's a party-based exploration game with a very unique feel. From the art design to the way your team deals with groups of natives to the vast array of character skills and development paths, this game has a lot going for it. Challenging enough for adults but accessible and appropriate for kids, this game is a great addition to any library. Whether you're resolveng encounters through a rock-paper-scissors approach which emphasizes non-violent conflict resolution or choosing what skills your characters develop while knowing that each choice can open up some new discoveries and make others all but impossible, this game has a lot of elements that keep you coming back for one expedition after another.", "appid": "296970", "steamid": "profiles/76561198035851397", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1511697600.0}
