{"text": "Spectacular game with another addicting story from telltale games. That really put me in the shoes of Bruce wayne the Batman, the gameplay was excellent and story driven, giving you varying characters choices (within dialogue) that overall don't change the end game but do give you a sense of control. The game does rely on quicktime events throughout the chapters giving some awesome scenes. The detective parts of the game were pretty basic but got you thinking of different simulations and outcomes. So overall the game was incredible but with a few dialogue choices that could be improved as they don't fit hundred percent of the time, but the story was great! I can't wait to play Batman: The enemy within. 8/10", "appid": "498240", "steamid": "profiles/76561198149001930", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1585483200.0}
{"text": "Old but still lots of fun. Great game if you enjoy carnage with your racing! Don't be fooled by the screenshots, it's not just carnage, there's plenty of proper (arcade) racing in this, but with highly destructable environments. Don't expect state of the art graphics, but do expect fun, smashy racing, perfect for when you want something more casual than a proper racing sim. Well worth buying when it's on sale, which it is right now in fact. Oh, and don't be fooled by my short playtime, I played this a lot years ago before I joined Steam.", "appid": "12360", "steamid": "profiles/76561197998031554", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "30", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561896000.0}
