{"text": "Following the events of Far Cry 5â€”having been seventeen years after the nuclear explosions rocked the plains and mountains in Hope Countyâ€”there rises another disturbance to the post-war, peaceful upbringing across the vibrant, magenta-flowered lands of devastated forestation and northern-lighted-colored skies of Montana. Players take control not of the Rookie from Far Cry 5, but as someone called the \"Captain\" as a dangerous gang called The Highwaymen are leading a devastating attack against a group known as Prosperity, led by Thomas Rush. Upon being separated from the leader and nearly drowning and left for dead, The Captain is saved by the daughter of Nick and Rye from its predecessor: Carmina Rye. Along with the citizens of Prosperity, Carmina is trying to restore balance and peace in this post-apocalyptic world, but they cannot do it without the Captain's help. Rumor has it that a new civilization known as New Eden has formed within the confines of the radioactive boundaries in Hope County, but the question is who is under their leadership? And what of the whereabouts of Joseph Seed and the Rookie? Who is Mickey and Lou and why are they hellbound on solving every problem with violence? Whatever the case may be, the answers will involve lots of exploration, crafting, upgrading, gathering, conquering, defending, protecting, and trusting the impossible as the Captain ventures into unknown territory to try and restore balance to the small world. Highly recommend this if anyone is a fan of the Far Cry franchise, especially the last one. The only complaint I have about this game are the micro-transactions; they should not exist because they entice the consumer to pay more than what is recommended. Pick it up on sale and if you want more Far Cry, and as always bring a friend to tag along and help.", "appid": "939960", "steamid": "profiles/76561197989790891", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "16", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created":