{"text": "*HUGE SPOILER WARNING* *YOU HAVE BEEN WARNED* So, the steam summer sale is a time to check out some games that you've always wanted to try but never really wanted to pay the price for/ never had the time to try them, for me Devil May Cry was one of those games. I have heard of this game in the past seen tidbits of gameplay for it but never really came around to it. There is so much I have to say on this games behalf as I have just finished my first playthrough which took me about 12 hours. I just have to simply say that this game completely blew me away. For starters it exceeded my expectations tenfold. I've always known hack and slash games for being fun for a little while and then getting very stale and boring very quickly but to be quite honest I'm still having just as much fun now as I was when I first launched the game. There are a plethora of good things that I have to say about this game so lets break some of that down. For Starters Let's talk about the game's progression: This game does a phenomenal job at timing. What I mean by this is, It incorporates each of it's weapons into play at what I find to be the perfect time. So you start out with your sword which is your \"primary\" weapon known as the Rebellion. Shortly after in the same mission (Mission 1) you recieve your dual pistols known as Ebony and Ivory which is considered to be your \"secondary\" weapon. So the next weapon you obtain is your first demonic weapon. So in a way this game's weapons are broken down into two types (three if you want to include guns) Demonic and Angelic. The first weapon that you recieve is a demonic weapon known as the Arbiter which is an axe that does an ungodly amount of damage (for this stage of the game) Because this weapon is obtained during mission to Very shortly after you are introduced to your first angelic weapon which is a scythe known as the Osiris, which isn't quite as heavy on damage but rather is a weapon that is considered to be ideal for crowd control. This weapon is introduced in the same mission as the Arbiter (Mission 2) and is the last weapon that is introduced for a bit. (More on the game later Lol)", "appid": "220440", "steamid": "profiles/76561198061892266", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1594555200.0}
