{"text": "If you like free-roam games and in general have an inner racer inside then The Crew 2 is definitely worth for you to consider.  The vehicle handling is great (however planes might take a little bit of practice to get the hang on).  If you have played The Crew you need to be aware that The Crew 2 has absolutely no storyline like the previous game, instead your main goal is to get followers to increase your popularity rank and to get rewards (this includes; vehicles, in-game currency, and new events across the map), and of course to beat the current champions in the game. There's also a lot of freestyle things to conquer, for instance skill events where you have to do certain things within a limited amount of time, you can also try to go for the world record in an event if you really wish to go hardcore.  On the more creative side people can even make their own liveries for their vehicles to give them a personalized touch which in my opinion is a nice extra feature. (When you first get started with the livery editor you can easily spend hours making that perfect livery for that specific vehicle of yours)  Overall a very nice game with plenty of gaming hours in it.", "appid": "646910", "steamid": "profiles/76561198024990117", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1530273600.0}
