{"text": "All I can say is wow. As a fan of Klei and everything that they do, I was not surprised by the incredible nature that this brought to the table. For a very long time I have loved Don't Starve (Together), as you can see by my 257 hours in-game, and I might have found a new favorite game. I am a type of person who loves games involving strategy and resource managing, and if you are a person like me, then you will LOVE this. The graphics are simplistic, yet detailed, similar to those in the Don't Starve series. The real world associations in this game including physics and health are extremely accurate and are only going to get better in the future updates. This game is amazing and I know it is going to get so much better in the future. Thank you Klei.", "appid": "457140", "steamid": "profiles/76561198273676898", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1495108800.0}
{"text": "Personally, I enjoyed it.  It's a simple relaxing solitaire game.  The music is soothing and Christmas-y.  Quite a lot of levels which lends itself to the one-more-turn syndrome.  And these levels add just enough variety not to make it too repetitive.  Different levels, based on the different card locations and number of shuffles lends a bit of strategy to where in the layout to focus one's matches. It's not without it's flaws though.  Card clicking can be frustratingly non-responsive and takes a bit of getting used to.  And the most annoying thing for me was the \"Earn 1,000,000 coins\" achievement which actually means you need to gather a total of 1,000,000 coins at the same time.  I mistakenly spent a lot of coins on upgrades and had to grind 100,000s of coins just to finish the final achievement.  If one is conservative with upgrades, you'll hit 1 million coins well before the finish at which point you can start spending like crazy to finish the last levels and get the \"Use XXX Upgrades\" achievements. Overall, despite it's flaws and simplicity, there is quite a bit of game time to it which made it worth it's asking price for me.  Not going to say it's a \"must buy\" or anything like that.  It could be more polished (see flaws above), but I enjoyed at as a nice casual game.", "appid": "428510", "steamid": "profiles/76561198119915053", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1514548800.0}
