{"text": "I ain't doing this review comparing Borderlands 1 with Borderlands 2, 'cause the first game will sound inferior, wich is not true, It's just very diferent Also, this is an Update for   which was made for the original and outdated vesion of Borderlands 1, this is the review for the   version Borderlands 1's Story is... Weak, with boring and irrelevant characters(in the Base game) that end up just giving random and irrelevant secondary quests, and some main quests. During the whole story it's promissed a vault filled with loot, well the vault itself doesn't have any loot, but you do get some good stuff, besides there is a boss fight that, unfortunetely, doesn't respawn, which is a problem, at least for me. Borderlands 1's maps are(most or them) desert themed, I do like their designs(Bandit camps mostly), but your opinion might be diferent. Most of the desert maps are quite big, and you're able to (in most cases) use vehicles(in base game, there's only one, in Knoxx's DLC there are 3). The maps that are not Desert usualy are Underground facilities or a Town/Camp, these tend to be smaller and, no vehicles allowed. Well... Playing alone can be boring, Because you really feel alone, with little dialog here and there from NPCs(honestly, there's very few), but all loot is yours... Hehehe In Co-Op you should have more fun, the game was meant to be played co-op. There's a looot of weapons to chose from, most of them do look the same, even though are diferent, the game's from 2009 and it's impressive the ammount of available weapons. What makes the weapons diferent, are their weapon parts, this makes certain weapons (legendaries, uniques, etc.)usually be, even if underleveled, better than new loot you find. To acquire legendaries or Pearllescents(DLC, included in the GOTY Enhanced) you'll need luck, a random world drop(random enemy, loot chests, vending machines) rather than a specific boss. If you're playing Co-Op, it's recomended that each party member plays a diferent character(class), each class is unique on their own, all have skill trees , that boost their respective action skill and weapons in many ways. There are Class Mods, that boost skills and add a special effect to the team or just yourself, such as Health Regen., bigger mag size, you get it. My biggest complaint with the game, it's the lack of farmable bosses, I know that I wouldn't compare BL1 with BL2, but in this case was needed The customization was improved from the original to this version, you can change colors and heads now. I have over 100 hours of game, my first character was Lilith(now lvl 69), and I felt like doing this, here is my score: 8,25/10", "appid": "729040", "steamid": "profiles/76561198207017241", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1558094400.0}
{"text": "REALLY LOVE THIS GAME !!", "appid": "582010", "steamid": "profiles/76561199003815632", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1588680000.0}
{"text": "Firstly this is a prequel to Life is Strange which i mostly avoided due to the time travel mechanic, my brain strongly dislikes being broken. So as a prequel you will have an idea of what will probably happen, but this game does not have the time travel mechanic which will be a negative for some and not for others such as myself who are thankful of its absence. So without the time travel wizzy do da surely this is just a choose your own story adventure? Yes but wait don't run away just yet... this one has fairly strong characters and a lesbian love story... no not like that, put your tongue away. Anyway the characters are fairly stereotyped as you would expect but it still can draw out some feels of many flavours as you go through the game. At best if you are interested in this part of the Life is Strange lore then dive right in, preferably blind, i first watched a whole playthrough but i was too deep at that point in the lore that i bought it anyway just so i could choose my own branches of dialogue. Like telling David to go F*** himself at nearly every opportuinity. I guess you're tired of this so let's rap this up... If you see value in story driven choose your own adventures with admittedly rather limited branches available, then give this sweet little roller coaster a try, just don't expect any adult patches but you can find plenty of cough cough fan art on the internet. Also you must be this tall to ride and remember you're at a fairground with moody teens so don't queue up thinking it's a opera, jeans and converse will do. Still not sure?...  watch this short video that shows some highlight moments (some small to medium spoilers)", "appid": "554620", "steamid": "profiles/76561198268063975", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "46", "votes_funny": "8", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561809600.0}
