{"text": "Rising Storm 2 is more than just the successor to RO2/RS. It has completely changed the game and improved upon the originals so much its hard to go back. RO2's launch was a damn mess. RS2 has continualy been updated and the devs have stayed in touch with the community. The game has a roadmap you can view for development, and everything they have promised they have delivered on. I am impressed beyond belief with the support this game has recieved, both from the devs and the playerbase, which is larger than its ever been in the RO series. Just about everything everyone who played RO2 speculated about has been put into practice. For years any kind of Viet Nam mod had been dead in the water for so long, the community had practically forgotten about it. And then RS2 started releasing videos. AKs, RPGs, M16s, Huey drops and Cobra strikes, the Dskh HMG, traps, tunnels, and tons of dense jungle combat. I was skeptical at first, RS2 didn't have a seamless release. There were serious bugs and hit reg was absolutely terrible. But they fixed it in a couple months, and haven't stopped fixing it and adding things since.  This game will test your situational awareness, your knowledge of cover/concealment, what you thought you knew aboput ballistics, and how many times you thought it was possible to die in one game. Perservere, ask veteran players questions, watch what they do, always give your machinegunner ammo and move slowly.  If you do even some of those things at the beggining, you'll probably be fine.  This game is small scale and large scale strategic teamwork, rolled into one, It is imcredibly rewarding, and you'll notice the impact certain people have on the battlefield.  I can't say enough good things about the game, its one of the most unique shooters I've ever played. Wtach some videos if you're still in doubt.  If you're looking for something a little more realistic than Insurgency or Battlefield, but you don't want to play ARMA, definitely check out Rising Storm 2. Edit: Well, now I can't say â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ about the devs supporting this game. Antimatter was bought out and this game is no longer going to be updated. It's still fun, but now its going to die a low death over the next 5 or so years.", "appid": "418460", "steamid": "profiles/76561197977417896", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1542801600.0}
