{"text": "A pretty fun and interesting take on a dungeon crawler. I haven't played too many Adult Swim games, but the few that I have played (Westerado:Double Barreled, Duck Game) & even the moblie game Robot Unicorn Attack 2 are all pretty well made games. But staying more specifically to WASTED, the idea of the game is you go through various dungeons looking for different \"Boozes\" that will give you \"Hangovers\". These hangovers when combined with other boozes throughout the game will make your charcter overall stronger. But this game does also have a Rouge-like element. Meaning, when you die, you lose your hangovers and buzzes. However, you can stash items throughout your adventures allowing you to start off with items when your charcter dies. However, I did feel that this game can feel a bit repetitive despite the fact the dungeons being randomly generated. It has a pretty good RPG element to it, which is something needed in Dungeon Crawlers. Also, like with most Adult Swim games, the soundtrack is catchy well made and goes along with the overall theme of the game pretty nicely. Also goes without saying, the comedy in the game is pretty on point, it's an Adult Swim game after all.  TL;DR: My overall oppinion of WASTED, is that it is a well construced Rouge-like Dungeon Crawler that will provide you with some well written laughs and gameplay that can keep you enthralled for hours to come, albeit slightly repetitive. However, if you like being presented with a challenge, and goin pew-pew, this game is for you. 4/5", "appid": "327510", "steamid": "profiles/76561197984320376", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1465300800.0}
