{"text": "The game starts off rather slow with seemingly uninteresting dialogue but picks up quite fast after the initial sequence.The pixel graphics are great but in my opinion the environment should be a bit more vibrant.Also some areas of the game are black or lack textures,maybe those will be added for the release of the game. This Prologue actually got pretty engaging towards the end but it still has a very slow pace. ''Ashina: The Red Witch Prologue'' has very light RPG elements.Only an inventory and a way to interact with certain items,doors,stairs and characters.I think this type of game should have a world that should feel alive and be more interactive.Maybe some small side-quests when running around trying to figure out the main plot,more NPCs interacting with the player in various ways or interacting with one another,maybe some small mini-games.When I saw the lake I thought I would be able to interact with it in one way or the other for example.The first map is quite small also,you can traverse it in probably 20 seconds.Obviously I expect the full game to have achievements,cards and more interactive stuff instead of just running around listening to dialogue. Animations are pretty crisp and coupled with the dialogue it certainly falls into the ''Anime'' category. Some observations I could make....the shaky camera.I don't know if it is intended but I believe the camera should move more smoothly when transitioning from one place to the other.Another thing is the option to actually leave a chat instantly without having to go through all the dialogue again.Maybe even an option to silence the sound when talking to NPCs.It is kinda annoying you can't save in this prologue also.One thing that should be added is a little hint on how to actually use the items because it's not quite intuitive and can be frustrating to some players.It can be easy to miss the fact that you need to access your inventory,click the item and then interact with the NPC in order to use it. When it comes to soundtrack and other in-game sounds,nothing special.Maybe the full game will have something else to bring to the table Overall the game looks decent or even good in some aspects,especially when it is only a Prologue or Alpha/Beta version of the full game that is scheduled to release sometime in 2021.", "appid": "1259180", "steamid": "profiles/76561198034782339", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1596542400.0}
