{"text": "This game was really one to play if you ever get the chance. It introduces new mechanics in a game where I would never expect. When I started, I thought it was very interesting getting to know the character's hardships and struggles and it got me immersed.  The graphics were beautiful and the scenes of the forest was stunning as you explored through them. It gets you paranoid when you advance deeper into the game hearing things around you and the story line itself.  You always feel like someone is watching you in the woods which is creepy. The story line had interesting contact and dialogues between 2 people, and it made it worth playing because you controlled each situation.  Although the ending could of been a lot different, I still loved it nonetheless even though you could kind of seen where the story was going. It was a brief short story, in which I finished in 4 hours.  This game has potential for a series like a prequal to give more backstory, instead of ending it abruptly without what really happens in the end with the characters because it really leaves you hanging.  But all in all despite the closing of the game, I would give this game a shot, it had good mechanics, good scenery, good story line, and definitely was one to remember.", "appid": "383870", "steamid": "profiles/76561198061553046", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1562068800.0}
