{"text": "The mission of this DLC was to tie together Bioshocks into a single story. Maybe the Irrational Games wanted to finish the series to work on something different, maybe they wanted to make the story indivisible, so 2k wouldn't mess it up with a next game, or maybe it was merely an alternative idea for the ending. I don't know, and I didn't google. As a result, BaS digs plot holes. This is expected when you're trying to sew together two pieces that were not meant to be one. The characters are redone to fit a new plot. The whole ending feels rushed and weak. Even the interior of the microscopic last level looks unfinished. The first part was good, but this one... it just doesn't feel right at all. But who knows, there is going to be a next Bioshock made by a different people and maybe you would hate it so much, that this DLC will look like the best thing ever. Maybe you should better delay playing it then. That's what I would do if I could.", "appid": "214932", "steamid": "profiles/76561198027491771", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1589803200.0}
