{"text": "I'm somewhat surprised at all the positive reviews for this all things considered, but it is with a heavy heart that I cannot give this dlc a good review at this time.  I want to badly, I really looked forward to this dlc coming out and eagerly dropped that 20$ on it, I gave the game itself a stellar review but I'm not pleased with Holy Fury.  Admittedly, I have not fully explored everything holy fury brings to the CK2 table, and while there are some notable improvements, there are even more glaring errors.  For 1, Paradox decided to erroneously tinker with Byzantine succession and somewhat with the Byzantine starting position.  this is major because it renders Byzantium pretty much unplayable; also it makes no sense whatsoever, considering every dynasty from that of Constantine I to that of Constantine XI operated under dynastic primogeniture-type succession.   the way it was set before as a/c primogeniture was much more accurate than some false, arbitrary invention like Byzantine electors.  Never did anything like this exist in the history of the Roman empire from Augustus to the fall of Constantinople.  Justinian was not elected.  None of the successors that are considered today to be of his dynasty were elected.  Heraclius was not elected.  None of his dynastic successors were elected.  The Isaurian emperors were not elected.  The Macedonian emperors were not elected.  The Komnenian emperors were not elected.  The Palaiologos emperors who reigned for the last 2 centuries of the empire were most definitely not elected.  So wtf?  I really have to wonder who thought this was a good idea or even remotely accurate, and I also question that individual's credentials for being involved with making a historical game like this, to have made such a mistake and been able to push it through.   Also, this dlc seems to have bugged or locked some achievements.  I definitely should have gotten \"I shed blood of saxon men\" on a charlemagne ironman run last night, but did not.  there could be others, I'm not sure yet.   The bloodline mechanic is novel and interesting but they made it overly difficult and convoluted and complex. Another issue, & I'm not sure if others have experienced this, but I'm having constant revolts for no reason.  even when there are no factions against me and when all vassals have a positive opinion of me, somehow a revolt pops, very shortly followed by another.  I even exited out and set the revolts to the lowest allowable amount with ironman, and they were still constant.  this has been happening to me probably within the first 20 years of the last couple games I started, so Idk if it's a glitch in the code or some weird error that's just isolated to mine or what but it definitely wasn't like this before Holy Fury.   Like I said before I really want to like Holy Fury but I can't right now.  It's an over-hyped dlc & they tinkered with things that should have been left alone, messed up some other things, and while yes there are some decent improvements here and there, they're mostly minor and cosmetic or an interesting novelty.  I haven't tried out the \"new\" crusade mechanics yet, but from I hear there are complaints there as well, although they're of the \"new crusades are OP\" variety as opposed to the \"crusades too weak/hard\" of yesteryear.  In my original review for CK2 I said there's a thousand thrills to be had in this game; I can't really say that Holy Fury adds anything substantial to that, at least for me at this point.  The new achievements are a cool addition but I'm kind of disappointed that I paid full price for this dlc, which makes a favorite game less enjoyable.", "appid": "756660", "steamid": "profiles/76561198164024043", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "38", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1544097600.0}
{"text": "If you're one of those people who thought Origins was a bad Arkham game, has Rocksteady got a surprise for you. So yeah, let's make an UE3 game look like it's using Cryengine 3, but let's definitely not buy a Cryengine license, cause money yo! If you have a card with 2gb of vram (if you have less, look the other way, the game will not run at all), be prepared to lower the settings to the bare minimum (that's right! all 3 settings, all of the 3 settings that are 3... THREE... 3... 3... 3, not 2, definitely not 4, but 3), lower the resolution below 1080p and expect huge fps dips and chugging and even complete pauses in gameplay (0 fps). This is always present in the driving sections, and often while gliding across the map or diving to take out an enemy. Can't turn off blur, depth of field, dynamic lights or shadows, film grain, chromatic aberration, you can just make your game look super blurry by lowering the textures, and have all these wonderful frame dropping filters on, to make your eyes bleed a bit more. Let's say a thing or two about the gameplay (after all I suffered through this game for 20+ hours so far) - It's a mix between the good old Arkham Asylum/City laser precise and very responsive combat, and some of the worst predator encounters I have experienced in an Arkham game, the enemy placement is a mess, there are too many enemies in every predator encounter I came across, and they decreased the number of ceiling grappling points drastically, so often you're in underground shafts or making those 2 ceiling grappling points work somehow. The story \"SO FAR\" is not great, I'm not enjoying it regardless of the frame rate. The Riddler challenges with the batmobile are either a puzzle or a race against the clock, the races are just horrible and tedious, puzzles are decent but not great, all in all the Riddler side quests are not that good. The open city batmobile sections themselves are totally unneeded, and battling the tanks while you're in the car feels like a mediocre Playstation 2 Japanese giant robot game, it's just tedious and dumb. I have to say though that the car does come in handy and is used in really interesting ways at times, but that's only in scripted main story moments. Voice acting and music are of course top notch, not a single complaint there. Catwoman looks hot! Oh yeah, you can unlock the 30fps cap imposed by Hitle... I mean by the devs, by editing an .ini file, but what's the point really? :) I'll update/rewrite the review and maybe even change the rating if I feel the game is actually worth buying when (more probably \"IF\") they fix this mess. So, unless you have an nvidia gtx 900 series card or a titan, I suggest you stay away from this game for now. edit: They actually increased the game's price by 5 euros. XD edit 2: and now you can't even purchase it from steam, because it's so damn unfinished.", "appid": "208650", "steamid": "profiles/76561198045132769", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "9", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1435060800.0}
