{"text": "Hi, I'm writing a review about this game forcibly, you'll understand more when I completed my review of this game called \"Blockstormâ€œ, I bought Blockstorm on December 1st for Â£3.59 from the steam store during steam sale Blockstorm was 60% off the original price Â£8.99, This game is in Early Access, I've been playing this game for a month exactly, I have 142 hrs on record playing this game, through my time playing this game I've had Mixed and up and down experience, though mostly down experience about this game, I bought this game because I'm a Huge and Major gamer mostly at FPS games and gaming in general, especially on the pc where I play allot of games, I bought this game as an alternative to Call of Duty, Medal of Honor, Battlefield and all the other typical FPS genre type of games these days and always wanted to try Minecraft heard its fun and all, though I don't know where to get Minecraft from, as upon I was looking the steam store page I saw this game and said this looks very much like Minecraft esque, more FPS styled Minecraft like game (from the video, images on the Store page of this game, and the actual Demo I then later played), I'm going to write more on the part of this review on the gameplay/game mechanic's, Developer's side and overall the game in general, I'll write about the positives first then the negatives later, still considering this is an Early Access game, this game initially from playing it, seems very exciting to me, just like anything in life is first time exciting, because first time I'm playing a game/FPS game stylised like this Graphically, At first it was eye catching, fun (though lost a bit, really working out if this is a Minecraft game or a FPS genre game), shooting players, setting up traps, using bombs, and various other in-game equipment (though not that many of a choice), then later on it became more of just Minecraft game breaking/adding blocks and building stuff and (more of the part when other players started to do the same digging and building blocks it drags you in as well to do the same),after killing/blowing up players, getting achievements and ranking up high, it started to get boring doing same thing over and over again (I guess this is the nature with games styled as this seems lacking in depth and dimension), in my experience of this game, I've played this game allot and thoroughly through I would strongly say since, I've played all the maps on the servers countless of times, Ranked highest in the game, completed majority of the achievements (achievements and Ranking system were later implemented around similar/same time in the game, I only realising this when I got an achievement in a match, no prior knowledge of this when launching the game, no update message), for the bugs end of this game I found many in this game, glitching through walls, escaping through the maps boundary (I have screenshots showing this), a developer I've communicated with while in game with, said this is the most substantive game out there for a game that is in Early Access, this does not seem all well for bugs I've seen though we'll see when final release of the game, the main menu of the game is fine looking I like it that its offset to the right slightly and not central, I think that's a nice touch, there is 5 options, then 3 Icons then a quit button, the 5 Options are Quick match, Choose match, Editors, settings and credits, these are all ok/fine, though I would say the Editors part need more to it, especially for people who are new to using programs for creating characters and maps, like instructions that's easy to understand by all, and the 3 Icons is Profile - where you can check your stats like k/d ratio, kills, deaths, assists and achievements, next icon is leader boards - where you can check your self where you rank amongst your friends and where globally against other players, and last icon is, community where you can see the forums. my final and main part of this review is about the developers part and their contribution to this game and their action/behaviour to the community and me, yesterday I've apparently been banned from this game from all official servers with no real explanation to as of why I've been banned, I'm very popular amongst many players in this game I play with, I'm known amongst the community, we get along well, though in the latter part of my days in this game the developers or certain people of the developers had a negative turn/outlook about me I don't know why is this so their communication with me became brittle and tarnished, I looked everywhere even my friend list on steam to find my no longer who was a friend, a developer who deleted me gone, we chatted well when we were friends and that's no longer now that he deleted me, I added a developer who was on steam and to my surprise he accepted my request, upon accepting my request he noticed I was online at the time and opened up to me first with \"what do you want?\" this clearly indicated to me their despise and their dislike to me as a person I'm very sure of this, I keep my cool and asked along the lines to \"why have I been banned\" I've as expected not much of a substantive answer of why I've been banned, \"all the conclusions have been concluded\" I still haven't been given a substantive answer, so I quizzed him further, he said he doesn't know, then said \"Happy new year\", then I said Happy new year back then he says he has to leave and said \"Goodbye\" then deleted me, (there was quite amount of tension in this conversion) so it wasn't a surprise at all, I looked in the forums all I can see people say I cheat/hack, and in game sessions some people say I cheat/hack is all I can find, though no real proof of it. This game is made by/heavily influenced by Italian games company most presumably by Italians, It is to be of expected from a country/nation that isn't well versed/cultured around gaming and gaming in general from the making side point of view to produce a games and games in general, I don't know any other games made in Italy a quick google search \"games made in Italy\" first link and you can see nothing surprising comes up, only see Assassin's Creed IV: Black Flag, this game was developed by Ubisoft Montreal (which is in Canada) and published by Ubisoft (Ubisoft a French games company) same with Assassin's Creed III: Liberation which is there also, though I think its there on the list of games made in Italy to respect with the games series/series early on which is set/cast in Italy or Italy has some or significance in relation to the games storyline. Other than that there isn't much with to Italy and producing games, this is clearly an oxymoron. Overall my final summary/conclusion of this game is that this is just another game about to launch on steam, seems exciting first with all the hype just like anything in life is first time is exciting, this is just Minecraft + Call of duty nothing more if I was to give a rating to this game itâ€™ll be 4 out of 10 for gameplay, any other rating for overall developers contribution/behaviour to the players and community would in this game it'll be near a 2 out of 10 overall or as Italy's performance at the 2014 World Cup in Brazil not making pass the group stages. Only greedy people wants to make money with all any other businesses no care for the people and customers only money is all care is for, criminally treat people like my self for example, though I can say this is good and bad, it has saved me from wasting my time and life on this game and I can move on and better spend my experience my knowledge in gaming elsewhere where it can be put to use, bad they lost a very well and potentential person in gaming who pretty much has all the knowledge they are looking for developing this game. I've been playing games for at least half of my life, Majority of my life, I've never cheated/hacked any game, never been banned from any game before and never thought I'd have to write a extensive review", "appid": "263060", "steamid": "profiles/76561198016008179", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "13", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1420027200.0}
