{"text": "The concept is appealing because it has that retro Astroids feel to it, however in its current state there is much more work to be done here to be in a completed state. What you can expect from this game: - One mode - Survival Mode. This mode is pretty brutal even on the first wave. The enemies are coming so fast at you that it will take a few times for you to even learn the controls for the game. But, once you're used to it, it gets a little better to avoid enemies and you learn to circle around them quickly but with how fast they are, you will hesitate to find to a time to shoot them down. If you're looking for a game that kicks your ass and challenging, this may be your speed. If you're looking for a casual game that is relaxing (with this currently being the only mode) I would not suggest. - Limited controls that are a bit awkward. There is not a tutorial yet or a mapping of controls, so as far as I am aware there is only the option to use the mouse to control your ship. Left button shoots while the Right is your directional button. This is awkward for me, and find it confusing when playing. I'd really like to see an option to change the controls to my own preferences. I would really like to make some suggestions or give my feedback for more about the game. I've tried looking into more about it, look into the Dev and find out what their plans are for the game. However, I currently do not see anything like that. As another reviewer stated, this is a game that would probably be better suited in Early Access on Steam. If you're looking for a complete game with packed features and various modes, I would not recommend.", "appid": "465190", "steamid": "profiles/76561198048998170", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1466596800.0}
