{"text": "Updated at 24h gameplay TL;DR: Purchased for 30 EUR (discount), but so far it seems to me it does't worth that much.  The game has functional coverage of a game, but missing the sense of actually playing it. After approx 50 missions it gets so repetative, it annoys me. Now I can't refund it, I will play through for achievements. This is a well-fledged director version. Can I give weapon to my agent? Yes, you can. Can I use special skills? Yes, you can. Is there a story? There is. Some players like collectibles, are there any? There are. Though they payed a good care with cold war time furnitures, I rarely see so well worked out aloe plant and wooden walls. Rusty barrels are state of art. Level design is fair and square, well done.  It has full XCOM engine for tactical missions, but lacks the integrity with interfaces or an immersion. Do you remember Commandos series from 2000? Now you can play it again with spy characters. Base is different, works like XCOM or at parts worse.  XCOM works fine, because it is a paramilitary strategy. Phantom Doctrine as intelligence warfare needs different mechanims. Not like \"Here, you recovered a new investigation piece for a case. This is the 3rd of 19.\" There could be sophisticated social engineering, civilian contacts/networks, several bartering. Not just time and money cost. This can be a good game, but needs (...much) more care and user experience touch. Others do better, go back to the desk, work on it for some months on. Please!  For the sake of the game! Even Klei with Invisible Inc. had the sense in there, and they did not want to shoot this far.", "appid": "559100", "steamid": "profiles/76561198044916896", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "9", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1543492800.0}
