{"text": "Heres the thing... For the price, it's definitely not worth it. The campaign was incredibly short, and while there is cross platform play, it is very hard to have a fun and competitive race with other players. Players refuse to join races as the wait times are too long, and the skill level is wildly diversified. You are pulled away from the campaign by level locks on missions, so you have to spend a considerable amount of time (and real money, in the future) grinding XP and currency to upgrade your car. By the time youve done that, you don't feel like playing anymore. The graphics are sub-par at best. I would even go so far as to say they were equivalent to predecessors like NFS Most Wanted, and NFS Rivals. In the future, I'm expecting incedible amounts of modders, farmers, and hackers. The game is very easily exploitable. While there seems to be a good amount of hype around the game, it left me with an unsatisfied \"This is it? I want my money back\".", "appid": "1222680", "steamid": "profiles/76561198180707354", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1593777600.0}
