{"text": "I am a veteran of Blitzkrieg (Blitzkrieg 1 and Blitzkrieg 2) and Sudden Strike (all games) series. One of My friends recommended Me this game, but it's gameplay is too slow for Me... Half an hour to rotate the tank; 5 second waiting after any of Your command to see any unit reaction... awful 3D... This game is really \"waiting simulator\" and patience training. Possibly, this game should be played 10 years ago, and for that time, it was good, but now - this game is awful. 3/10", "appid": "46290", "steamid": "profiles/76561198067692560", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "30", "votes_funny": "6", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1537790400.0}
{"text": "I am disappointed in anything in this early access as it is close to bare bones and pretty rough with almost nothing making it stand out from the rest of the competition so far with all the rogue-like games we've had that are in early access. I paid for an early release so I know what I am getting myself into to support the game and devs. If you're going to buy an early access and expect at least over 5 hours then this is not it. Since Steam doesn't support an in-between I am going to have to go with a thumbs down for those planning to purchase an early access that would have a bit of gaming time to sink time into otherwise you are just tossing money to support. Think about it, the original Rogue Legacy came out in 2013 not even an EA game sold over hundred thousand copies, now the sequel is out in 2020 as an EA and as raw as can be, there has been plenty of roguelike games plenty in between released in Early Access with even more contents than this and if you didn't know this you've been in your mancave hiding too long doing who knows what. I've seen way too many early access tools who debates with the same \"Well, its EARLY ACCESS what you expect\" phrase, no â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ sherlock. What I like about this game so far seen or what they will do is that it sticks to its original formula while adding randomization of levels biomes, traits, and better art. The gameplay is just as challenging even more but so far nothing special that has made stand out from the rest in this time and age and thus so far its  RL1 with better graphics with level randomization and a few character traits and classes.  Upgrades to the castle are also limited at the moment , unfortunately, no other biomes than just the one castle you run around in with a limited amount of enemies and a boss. Once you get the two magic items that are hidden in cleverly designed levels and crossed into the bridge you'll get the message about the things planned for this game which is a bridge biome while also taking a VERY SMALL sneak peek at the ice biome seeing lots of great ideas here and development plans but just not implemented yet.  Once you upgrade and git gud you'll finish in no time less than 2 hours. It'll be 60 days before we see a patch with more updates so BUY THIS GAME IF YOU SUPPORT the developers just don't expect much content yet.  I Will reserve my thumbs review for the final product itself. TLDR? An early access game so raw that even the hentai game in early access I'am playing has more content. I'll toss this on the side until the game is updated or done and hopefully my house doesn't get hit by  a meteor by the time it finishes so i can enjoy.", "appid": "1253920", "steamid": "profiles/76561197970487939", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "10", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1597752000.0}
