{"text": "I played a fair amount of this game and I loved every minute of it, the untranslated map, the poorly translated quests, all of it.  I am, no joke, a huge fan of the janky and confusing gameplay of these stalker style games.  The way they handle factions, weapons and magazines, anomalies and such are have a suprising amount of depth. This brings me to why this game is pure trash, and its the pay2win nature which isn't even fully implemented yet, it will only get worse from here.  There are so many weapons and armor in this game, but so few are actually accessible.  The grind wall is the most absurd I have seen in any game.  Here are some examples, these numbers are not fudged. A spas-12, a fairly cheap gun compared to some of these others.  Costing 3.3 million rubles and 10,500 trade points. Getting this gun only takes 100 straight days of doing a single mission twice daily. (which isnt actually possible given it has a 12 hour cooldown) A SIG SG550, very expensive at 7.4 million rubles and 90,000 trade points. Getting this gun takes a mere 895 straight days of doing a single mission twice daily. (the same one from above, also buying anything with trade points consumes them) If all they did was cut the trade point cost of most items in the game by literally 95% then I would actually recommend this game, as it is now your weapon choices are incredibly limited.", "appid": "1180380", "steamid": "profiles/76561197963512105", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1579694400.0}
