{"text": "So that's it ... Payday 2 I've heard a lot of positive from the series and the developer. I had now expects a clever and tactical robbery shooter. However, I was disappointed with increasing playing time. First ... the general mechanisms are good, they have improved a lot from its predecessor. Shooting is liquid, there are now a lot of variety in the Heists and many ways to customize your character. BUT: - There is no real housing system, even though it was announced as a slightly larger feature - Especially on higher difficulties, the enemy masses are completely unrealistic, even for the game  - There are seldom very demanding tasks, and there are not really demanding full teamwork - The skill and perk system cooperate unintuitive, one solid system would been better - The stealth missions are very sparse designed, and are difficult to briefing too - Almost all the stuff have to be found by chance and then you have to buy them only, the prices are astronomical too  - Due to the rapid leveling you may quickly feel at some point, that everything loses all of its value and feels inflated - Nearly the half of the complete gametime I was stuck in the lobby, permanent host changes etc.  - After a while, I see no sense to continue playing, my motivation is quickly at the end, because in so much menus are dozens purchase DLC buttons. I find this to be not so bad if there were 2 or 3 great DLCs and at least more game items than DLC items. But there are dozens of them and even some of them containing Heists and thus separates the players from each other... For me as a developer, the worst part is that OVERKILL has not kept his promise for no microtransactions. Even worse, all players were ripped cleverly. The devs presented themselves well, where others were in the controversy. Sold as many copies as possible and now that everyone has it and the source of income runs out, they squeeze out the last bit. And the sad thing is, it's now too late to do something about it, which could force improvement. Or maybe I'm wrong", "appid": "218620", "steamid": "profiles/76561198006425019", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "24", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1446465600.0}
