{"text": "Look IM trying to like this game, but there's so many things I have to do in the game, manage food intake and equipment weight, sickness, wetness, stamina, health, and theres literally a system for goin to the loo. However this is not even the farthest part that bothers me in this survival game.  -Zombies are laggier and much more annoying than in Dayz, and thats just sad for one. -Gunplay is strange an not refined, its fun but alot of things could be optimized about it and making it smooth should be a large goal. -Graphics are pretty good but they run pretty poorly on the scale, most people are running medium to low, and alot of the good looking effects are traded off for player vision. Losing alot of the fidelity and high end graphic work. -Animations in general are unresponsive and laggy, glitchy and not to mention some are just locked in place, not able to cancel and get gunned down, not being able to react while takin a piss, eating, jumping through a window, over a wall, hell bows are pretty much useless in this laggy mess. Don't even get me started on melee. The improved boxing and melee is cool but the animations are so f'ed up its basically impossible to even use them. If they have a gun, yur f'ed.  -Cars are pretty rare but work much better than in Dayz. They still lag around and cause some big FPS drops however.  -Building is cool and I would love to have a group to sit down and explore this area with but I can't really get passed all the other crap clogging the gameplay to even want to invest in building.  -Customization is cool but really basic and the skills are pretty interesting but restrictive and everyone is basically meta slaving on skill points. -And Finally, Loot. The loot in this game imo is trash and needs to be redone. So many materials and not enough things to properly defend myself. I will take the time to run many Kilos and not find a single gun in an entire military compound. And it wasn't even touched before I got there. The food options are trash especially if we're supposed to maintain healthy lifestyles like in real life, all I ever find is cheese and f'kn lime soda, pumpkins and other bs.  Verdict. Buy on sale, or wait for further development. The game has some cool systems and it is fun sometimes but there's def a large portion of the game needing to be reworked or finished. Not to mention alot is needed to be added, more customization items, hell, more impressive modding would be really nice and I'm sure just like with Dayz it would improve the gameplay and playerbase a ton. It sure saved that game.", "appid": "513710", "steamid": "profiles/76561198030795262", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "9", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1587470400.0}
{"text": "The concept for the game is great, and the gamplay mechanics, story, and atmosphere are all great too. However, the game has been in Early Access for a long time now, and little progress has been made. Until the game comes out, I don't recommend it just quite yet. Although I am confident when it does come out it will be pretty good.", "appid": "236370", "steamid": "profiles/76561198090591159", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "36", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1465560000.0}
