{"text": "I'm an immense fan of the Castlevania series, that is up until the Lords of Shadow entrants. The series has never done terribly well in its forays into the third dimension and even though this game is technically 2D it falls into all of the same pitfalls that Lords of Shadow does. What pitfalls are those? It wants   to be God of War. That's a problem because I don't like much God of War either. Both games suffer from a series of major issues. They have dull combat with mushy, impactless attacks that just kind of wave a fan at the enemy until they either get cooled off enough to have a lie down and nap off a hard days being wooshed, or until they flash to arbitrarily signal its time to do a quicktime event, or push a button and watch something intended to be gruesome happen to them. Those events are already a bit tedious to me but you throw in Mirror of Fate's lackluster visuals, amateurish presentation, schizophrenic camera that will give you motion sickness and generally humdrum design and you've got yourself a crappy Castlevania game. The movement is floaty and imprecise, grabbale ledges which are already a big no-no to Castlevania are magnetized and suck you in, you break barrels instead of candles, your attacks are whiffy and weak feeling, dodging has no iframes that I could see, blocking is rarely useful as 75% of attacks are unblockable, and navigation feels like they just give the illusion of free roaming much of the time. Perhaps I'm simply not the target audience, and I know I haven't gotten very far into the game yet but I'm extremely disatisfied with it. If I hadn't gotten this on sale for $3 from GamersGate I'd probably feel ripped off. I realize it's a port of a port of a 3DS game but the game itself is just not terribly appealing. If you're a fan of the oldschool Castlevanias ranging from the NES entrants to Symphony of the Night (which I still play through once almost every year) to the last decent release in Harmony of Dissonance, this is probably not going to whip your torches.", "appid": "282530", "steamid": "profiles/76561197970414676", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1454932800.0}
