{"text": "It feels like the devs had a cool concept (a puzzler about changing gravitational directions), then very quickly realized they didn't have many ideas for actual puzzles to make with it. Because of this the game is rather short, and not really interesting to be honest. You've got cutscenes trying to convince you there's more depth than I felt there was, and a new game+ that's the same game only the puzzle keys are in minorly different locations. Another thing is while the game isn't really about platforming, there are a couple places that require you to jump from an edge at nearly the farthest spot you can go before you start falling off, which surprised me a great deal. Perhaps my frame-rate messed with the physics just enough to be noticeable there? Either way, I sadly can't really recommend the game.", "appid": "812160", "steamid": "profiles/76561197996510707", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "12", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1583668800.0}
