{"text": "A great game, ruined by bad controls. The controls of a breakout game are probably the simplest in ANY game. There is left, there is right, and there is a button to launch the ball. That's it!.. VERY difficult to mess up, but Ironsun Studios managed to do just that. The movement is clumsy and unresponsive. At first I thought there was something wrong with the sensitivity, then I noticed how the bar wouldn't move at all, unless the mouse was moved at a certain speed. The developers put in deadzones!! They seriously put time and effort into making it unresponsive to small movements. If you have ever played a breakout game, you know that small movements are extremely important for being able to hit the ball at the right angle. Aiming goes out the window, and it gets even more frustrating when you loose a life, because the bar just didn't move, even though you actually moved the mouse. The game looks fun and all, but it's a constant frustration that you can't move the bar in a natural fluent way. It's a real shame. The game would have been fun to play, had the control not been massed up. If a fix comes out, please let me know. For now I can't recommend this game. Edit: Thread about the mouse problem:", "appid": "287120", "steamid": "profiles/76561198135792443", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "32", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1530014400.0}
