{"text": "I am here after about 3 hours of getting the stupid game to work.  The game has three major points of failure. Here has been my process. Buy game through steam. Download and update through steam. Launching the game actually launches Ubisoft's terrible UPlay. Uplay then asks for the activation key, which I then enter. Uplay attempts to redownload the entire game. I cancel it. Uplay now has 2 entries in the games list for anno; one for steam and one I'd have to redownload. I click the other one, and it launches through steam (yes, steam launches uplay which launches anno through steam). Anno then decides to update. There are now 3 updaters for this ONE game. Anno launches, and once again asks for my cd key (why??) and for me to log into uplay (although I *launched* this from uplay). It crashed a few times after this, but finally it took my cd key and told me that I have to restart anno to access the DLC; it gave me no choice than to restart the game. I restarted the game, and it took several attempts to even connect to their server to download the DLC. In sum: This game will only  work if steam, uplay, and the anno servers ALL work and are responding, and the process of even activating and authenticating yourself as a customer is hell. I haven't even gotten to play the game yet, because I just spent 3 hours of jumping through DRM hoops.  Do not buy.", "appid": "48240", "steamid": "profiles/76561197970202048", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "10", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1388059200.0}
