{"text": "I have a LOT more than my 1,157.3 hours show on STEAM. Been playing the game since damn near release. Have multiple accounts and have lost many nights of sleep on this game. So why do I not recommend? Easy answer: Since it became a \"free\" to play game, it has gone so heavily toward pay to win that it actually makes me sick. You used to have to actually spend time earning ISK and learning the game. Now, anyone with a credit card can download and have a character with millions of SP (skill points) in a matter of minutes. No, that doesn't make up for experience, usually, but when John Smith can pull out a credit card and easily get what others have worked long and hard to earn, its just pathetic. You can not compete with players that spend LITERALLY thousands upon thousands of dollars each month... hell, each WEEK. You PvP against them and win, they just come back with more real money items they bought. Eventually they wear you down and you run out of resources where they wont, simply because they just pull out their mommy and daddies credit card and *POOF* they instantly have everything they lost, plus some. The game used to be a blast, now its just \"Who can spend the most real money to get ahead\". Quite sad and pathetic. Wont be looking back after removing this game.", "appid": "8500", "steamid": "profiles/76561197996947462", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1605700800.0}
