{"text": "Utterly â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥.  Humble often gives games that doesn't make sense but I am amazed how they managed to make a crap out of basic tower defense.  You have to control your units by dragging their flags (Actively, more than often. You just can't put them around there and relax) and also you have to fight a â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ horde of bunnies. Flags + horde of bunnies = You can't see a â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥. UI and overall gameplay mechanics are just bad. That is what makes the game hard. Plus I don't want to mention how easily your tower is destroyed when a couple small â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ bunny reaches to it by leaking out their way. They could actually make a good game based on economy and strategy. At the first sight I thought this game was alike to Kingdom series. It turned out a basic tower defense, but a bad one. You just spawn soldiers, drag them around try to control rabbit population meanwhile trying to repel them as they make their way to your tower. I can't see much about strategy or economy here because I was unable to pass level 3 or 4. Tutorial doesn't help at all. Achievements' percentage tells the tale.", "appid": "777880", "steamid": "profiles/76561198075742770", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1579608000.0}
