{"text": "Bought this game in preperation for Metal Gear Solid V: The Phantom Pain. Was under the impression that it was a full game, but it essentially amounts to a $20 Demo. There is one level, and you can complete the main campaign mission within 5 minutes. Several side missions are unlocked after you complete the main mission once.  In total, the game will provide you about 1 hour of entertainment as you quickly burn through each side mission, all within the exact same map. The gameplay is fun, and proves to be a nice break from the linear progression we have come to expect from Metal Gear Solid games, leaving me in anticipation for the full release. But as a Demo, it's worth about $5 at most. Although I might have expected it to be free too, as is the case with so many other game demo's.", "appid": "311340", "steamid": "profiles/76561198003558926", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "11", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1438776000.0}
