{"text": "Right off the bat I have two issues with the game apart from performance. First off the game seems to run a shader compilation process which took close to 40 minutes to me. This is a first for me, no other native PC games I've played visibly compile shaders at first boot like emulators do. The second issue I have is how some cutscenes are seemingly locked in 30 FPS, while others are completely unlocked. If this is a case of pre-rendered vs in-engine custscene then it's a minor issue but still jarring nonetheless.  Performance-wise I can say this game is bizarre. Went with Ryzen 1600 and a GTX 980 but I only got 45 FPS on medium 1080p. Changed it to Digital Foundry's settings but I only saw minimal improvements. I ended up with 55 on low. Definitely seeing weirdness in the game's optimization since my build's well above the recommended settings. Devs are listening to the issues though, so I'll update my review as it's being fixed. For new buyers: best to wait for patch, or test the waters to see if your build has no issues with the game.", "appid": "1151640", "steamid": "profiles/76561198135186315", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1596888000.0}
