{"text": "I purchased the game on sale, used to play on consol and thought hey--for $10.00 heck yeah I would love to start up again on PC... only problem is that only AFTER you download the game you find out it requires you also install 'Battleye' anticheat software to play.  Now, a lot of games have anticheat software, so on the surface this looks fine--right? WRONG. 'Battleye' is incredibly intrusive software that gives the dev/dev's at Battleye complete access and, if wanted, total control of your system. In an ideal scenario it would only send snapshots of active processes, but it actually sends your listed IP and send disk-level data and files that are stored indefinitely on Battleye servers. So if you have some pissed off Dev who hates his job he can easily copy everything over from your disk and even worse he can actually execute programs on your system.  I'm extremely pissed off that I just wasted $10.00 for a game that wants me to install what is essentially intrusive spyware. Extremely disappointed as I loved this game on consol and was planning to play the crap out of this title until they made installing Battleye a requirement for PC.  P.S. -  it's now required for UNOFFICIAL servers as well so there's absolutely no way around the invasive Battleye requirement.", "appid": "346110", "steamid": "profiles/76561198035566107", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "89", "votes_funny": "38", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1604836800.0}
