{"text": "This is a review for the Reboot of Defiance, the Third Person Looter-Shooter MMO based off that forgettable now cancelled TV show.  This is the same exact game, but worse. Period. No new content, inferior systems, and all of the old problems.  I am a Defiance veteran, from the Original game. Clocking in over 2.3K hours on it. I have $40 spent. I reached the max level of 6000, something very few have been able to do. I was a prominent community member. I wanted the game to succeed. The game did not recieve an content update in 2-1/2 years, we were all hopefull for some announcement from Trion to save the game.  20 Inventory slots. Thats all I got, for all my time in the original. My original account had 160.  20 Inventory slots. Promises of a brand new engine, new graphics, reworked base game, and redesigned systems. 20 Inventory slots. Promises of no Power related Microtransactions. The store is loaded with them. 20 Inventory slots. Player progression reset. 2.3K hours of progression and min maxing  20 Inventory slots. Same Horrible lag and bugs that have ALWAYS plagued the original.  20 Inventory slots. Reworked player progression to be much much harder, power is easily gained from purchases. The original game was already P2W. This is the same game but worse. If you did not like the Original, you will hate this. If you did like it, come back in 2 years. See if the servers are still running and if Trion made it out of this fantastic mess they put themselves in.  They say they will steadily update the game, add more content. You had 2.5 years to do that Trion. 2.5 Years to not â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ up.  You pissed off a LOT of fans Trion.", "appid": "743090", "steamid": "profiles/76561198176854822", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "576", "votes_funny": "37", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1531483200.0}
