{"text": "There's another game from the same developer called \"Achievement Clicker\". So the first thing i thought was \"ok, this is gonna have new graphics, music and features, since it's the new version of the same game\". I was so wrong. The 2019 version of this game is IDENTICAL to the old version. Same graphics, same music, same mechanics. So, since the developer was so lazy to do a minimally different game, i'm gonna be as lazy as him, copying and pasting the same review i made for the other version of the game. First of all, this is not a game. It's a little program in which you have to click on a button to raise your points and gain achievements. That's all. This \"game\" has 5000 achievements, that you gain in a few minutes just clicking on the big button and buying upgrades to raise your score faster. There is a repeating music (which is cute, but annoying after a few minutes), which also stops after a while because the game is bugged. At the end i should say: play it only if you want easy achievements for your Steam profile. Pros: + 5000 easy achievements Cons: - Minimal and effortless graphics - Repeating and annoying (bugged) music - Very short - Not a game", "appid": "824190", "steamid": "profiles/76561198003090423", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1593691200.0}
