{"text": "If you're looking for a \"Papers, Please\" 2, this is not for you. Weeks of repetitive ID checking, where nothing changes, unlike PP where things change almost daily. You will go on auto-pilot after awhile since it's just so natural, or fall asleep, like I did. The storyline is very boring. It doesn't progress fast enough to keep your attention. It will take multiple days before anything remotely exciting happens. Things happen in the \"outside world\" that have no bearing on your job, unlike PP where something new happened almost everyday and it actually had consequences on your gameplay and job. I found myself not even checking the news app on my phone eventually and skipping entire text after the 20th day as I was so bored. Not challenging. This game is very easy and there is little penalty for screwing up (unlike PP where your entire family will die if you make mistakes). There is virtually no penalty or reward for accepting bribes, and if you make a mistake, you lose like, what, 3 pounds per?  Money is of little value since you make so much of it; accepting or rejecting bribes barely affects your game anyway. There is little risk in not doing the \"morally acceptable\" thing... unlike, again, Papers, Please. There's goals for hitting your first, second, and third objective. Sometimes you won't hit your third due to crappy RNG and you'll  have people who try to come in with fake IDs or people you will need to reject for other reasons. If you say no to them once, sometimes they will give you money and make you reject them a second time. I've had nights where I've had this happen four times in a row. This shaved off an hour of my already short 4 hours (4 minute) window. Needless to say, I did not hit my third objective sometimes, and not because I was \"slow\", but because the RNG completely messed with me, and time does not pause when you have people there who ask you to take their ID a second time after being rejected.  Also, they ask you to reject underage people. The ONLY underage person you will ever encounter is an annoying underage girl that drops by frequently, and this is the only time out of any night where you actively need to click the dialogue boxes to get the text flowing. This can be a hinderance when you're working fast to reach your goals and are sitting there, staring at the hand on the bottom left and wondering why an ID is not being given to you. While this isn't a big issue, when you've already got into the habit of simply rejecting/accepting people and having the text boxes move on their own, it can be a bit annoying when, for the first time in 3-4 nights, you need to suddenly click to let this stupid, pointless, meaningless text progress. Time doesn't freeze for this so if you don't click to progress the dialogue boxes, you will lose precious time, which you already have an incredibly short amount of. All in all, if you're looking for Papers, Please 2, this isn't the one. If you're looking for an engaging game that is challenging and interesting (and has nothing to do with PP), this is also not the one.", "appid": "733790", "steamid": "profiles/76561198091396513", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "37", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1548331200.0}
