{"text": "At start it seems like fun. A Free 2 Play PUBG with some added bells and whistles. Then you get familiar with the game and realize that this is one of the worst Battle Royales that exist. Horrible connection as in you have no idea of who they prioritize. The amount of times you go down a second after you knocked down the same person who knocked you is astonishing. Connecting bullets and melee hits always feels slightly off and weird. A guy swung a bat 2 meters away from me and I went down with full health 3 seconds after the swinging animation finished. The creme de la creme is that that very bat is something only available to people willing to shell out 20 euros. This game is loaded with microtransactions, all of them unfair. It's a free 2 play, sure it has microtransactions, but Fortnite is Free 2 Play as well and they made billions of cosmetics. The bat is not a cosmetic, it comes with other stats that are stronger than your default knife. You can buy characters with better abilities, but clothes with slight stat boosts, not to mention if you are a person who doesn't like looting you can always just buy a flare gun to start the game with (You shoot it in the sky and it drops down rare and top tier loot always). I want to love this game, but it's like trying to love a chocolate cake with beautiful icing filled with â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥. It looks like something you would enjoy, but then you cut a slice and disgusting â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ pours out, yet you force yourselves to take a bite every time you press the â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ play button. To sum up, this is the game that would give Tencent a raging hard on!", "appid": "884660", "steamid": "profiles/76561198052972956", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1581595200.0}
