{"text": "I never write reviews but I've never been more disappionted. The audio is a mess. There is one Master volume slider. The problem you have with that for this game is there are a lot of different types of sound and the mixing is garbage. The music feels way to slow half the time because there's a suprising amount of sleepy time Drone that the trailer and most reviews never mention. The noises your beetle make for doing something good drowns out everything. Audio cues get drowned out by everything (honestly that doesn't matter because this game is more about remembering the course since when to do a thing is so disconnected from the Music you can literally play on mute and lose nothing because this is not a rhythem game) To me a Rhythem game is when the music and when to do an action feel connected, and in a really good Rhythm game you feel like you could be blind and pull it all off because the sync between what you're doing and what you're hearing feels so damn good. This is not that game.  By an hour and a half I was just tired of \"racing\", aka just rembering a course, over bedtime music with almost no sync all while not hearing audios ques and dreading to do perfect turns because the chime was so damn loud and happy. Oh but it looks pretty so that's nice (because the most important thing in a Rhythm game is how good it looks)", "appid": "356400", "steamid": "profiles/76561197981889286", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1539172800.0}
