{"text": "This games trailer has so much goodness, I bought the game. Started the game, seems cool, saw a nice world map, found out it is actually pretty small. (ie, scale) I really wanted to like this game, but far to many things need to be addressed before it can be any fun. A few of the biggest problems I had with the game so far: 1. Zero in game explanation on anything. (like: how to get rid of tree stumps, how to move placed items, how to feed/rest/etc. chimeras; etc.) 2. Little to no direction, bad pacing, progress. (I have no idea how to progress at moment, beyond just mindlessing leveling, no goal) 3. The resource gathering 'tiers' are pretty far up on the skill tree, and if you didn't go directly to them, you will be wasting many hours grinding exp to make up for your mistake. Some minor problems: 1. Buildings exterior are all far too similar, too 'square', and/or not enough softness or round edges. 2. U.I. could use some work. 3. Can't dash/run during combat. (at least you stop running/dashing when combat starts, you can't just run past enemies sometimes) 4. Enemies can attack you across the map, and some have homing attacks. 5. Always always out of mana. 6. Farming at its current stage is far too basic. 7. Npcs disappear (they actually teleport) to their scripted location on their timetable. (I understand it will take some time to program/develop the game to a point to get the npcs to walk to their destinations, like in Stardew) 8. Your home map has a very big black/inaccessible square in the middle. 9. Some crafted items icons in the crafting screen have different visuals then their placed on ground visuals, so you can waste material making an item you all ready have. (ie: workbench.. thingy) 10. Equipment management and swapping is a little tiresome. 11. Inventory/Chest management is a little tiresome. (need some sort of automation, or 'quick sort to chest from inventory' button. Some good points. 1. Overall, great pixel art. 2. Lore/World. Can't go wrong with magical stuffs really. I would say the game has potential, but it is far too early in development at the moment.", "appid": "1070860", "steamid": "profiles/76561198034563233", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1605614400.0}
