{"text": "An absolutely dreadful experience, so much so that I quit this DLC mid way, something I rarely do, if ever.  Both of the DLCs are extremely buggy and broken, from cutscenes that make no sense at all, to sound bugs making conversations end abruptly or go silent. It is a botched mess.  The missions are basically a collection of tedious fetch quests and fort attacks that amount to nothing but the most boring repetitive chores.  Invade fort after fort, and you're done.  The way elysium is built in chapter one, is horrendous, they made the terrain extremely hard to navigate just to slow you down and give you the impression that the DLC is longer than it is. They do that but forcing you to climb and run endlessly. This expansion is downright insulting.  The Odyssey expansions are also blatant reskins of the Origins expansions, but much worse ones.  Which made it even more boring for someone like me who's played those.  It is everything the great base game isnt. After the base game leaving me wanting more, I played this and it ruined my memories of the base game and made me question if I even want to play another AC. It's that bad.  The worst, most boring most repetitive an AC game has to offer, packed into a DLC.  Stay away from this, or it'll hurt what you think of the whole franchise.", "appid": "937892", "steamid": "profiles/76561198070316379", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "20", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1573128000.0}
