{"text": "After spending 1h tweaking and playing tutorial multiple times I finally got the game to work and run smoothly. Had to play tutorial so many times because of crashing and glitches it was hard to get to the first save point. There were doors that didn't let you get through without nvidia control panel tweaks. Here are my tips: 1. Download WIDESCREEN FIXER. You find it using google. This is a MUST as it lets you tweak FOV. It messes up a few cutscenes a bit, but it doesn't really matter because the default fov is unplayable small. 2. Before launching the game go to nvidia control panel and enable TRIPLE BUFFERING and VSYNC to deadspace.exe . This is a MUST. 3. In the game set vsync OFF. This is a MUST. 4. Use GAMEPAD. Mouse and keyboard controls are HORRIBLE. I can now play the game and so far I have enjoyed it, but I won't recommend it because you need to do unoffical fixes to get the game to work.", "appid": "17470", "steamid": "profiles/76561197973353172", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1495368000.0}
