{"text": "Far Cry 5 is peak Ubisoft... and that's not a good thing.  I'd say something about the gameplay mechanics of FC5 but if you've ever played an open-world Ubisoft title you know exactly what to expect: by-the-numbers checklisting, going from waypoint to waypoint, doing the bidding of obnoxious dry characters until you've cleared an area of all map icons, rinse and repeat ad nauseam. Now a \"checklist-em-up\" isn't a bad thing per se but once again Ubisoft manages to make the whole thing feel so uninspired by not bringing anything new to the table or daring to shake up the formulae.  It takes itself far too serious and when it doesn't it just comes of as juvenile and tone-deaf. It's been a while since I've been this apathetic towards a story and its characters but when all was said and done I couldn't care less. Once the umpteenth slog of a cutscene came on I just found myself skipping through most of them towards the end of the game (something I actually never do). They're all pretty much the same thing anyway: characters droning on about how some higher power has instructed them to do the evil thing they're meant to do and how you, the silent protagonist, has a part to play in all of this. So they keep abducting you but then cut you loose again for reasons... Ok. There's no denying the game itself looks nice and the gunplay & movement are all solid but apart from that I'd be hard pressed to come up with any memorable or genuinely fun moments. Oh and to make matters worse this was meant to be a co-op game for me and a buddy but half the time that feature didn't even work and when it did it only seemed to save character progress for the host.  Far Cry 3 was great, FC4 already felt a bit too similar but was still enjoyable but FC5 is just too much of the same.  4/10", "appid": "552520", "steamid": "profiles/76561197968385902", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1598961600.0}
