{"text": "I played this game for 68 hours in 5 days, creating two characters with one of them reaching level 98 and beginning endgame raids and pushing through the season 3 grind. The earlier stages of this game are genuinely fun which kept me addicted, playing with a group of friends and helping each other out with leveling, it was becoming my favourite MMO with every hour until we got closer and closer to the endgame content. The endgame is a load of â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ with zero purpose or meaning, i love economy in games, earning money and grinding out weapons and legendary items to earn cash and bragging rights is a lot of fun. ONCE YOU REACH LEVEL 90 THEY GIVE YOU SOME OF THE BEST GEAR IN THE GAME IN A PACKAGE. The game has a face only a mother can love, the people who spent hundreds of dollars on this game and cant let this trash go and continue to farm the same dungeon over and over again with no end goal in mind. Speaking of money - ITS P2W !!! ... the only way to get better gear then the equipment given to you at level 90 is to push boss gear to +12,+13,+14,+15 to gain bonus stats. Gear has a chance to totally EXPLODE upon a failed enhancement, and getting to those end tier enhancements are really hard, with a cool way to get around it being.... PAY MONEY TO GUARANTEE IT DOES'NT EXPLODE, 'Premium Armour Enhance Runes' (13USD) can be purchased for when the enhancement fails, the item doesn't poof BUT the rune itself doesn't disappear either so you can spam the â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ out of that enhancement button until it does. THATS JUST ONE EXAMPLE, VIP and VVIP systems are there as well as if the game is some bad mobile app, granting bonus loot, damage, and exp for dungeons. OH!!! and when you complete Season 3 they give you +15 accessories as well, ruining the only slot left to enhance and gain yourself after you hit level 90... This game is for little kids who cheat in Skyrim to get the best gear and stop playing after 2 hours because they got bored. Some of the raids are fun in a party. Especially when a team member spends 20$ on revives to revive the ENTIRE party.", "appid": "212160", "steamid": "profiles/76561198014906447", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": "5", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1575892800.0}
