{"text": "It can often be surprisingly entertaining, refreshing even, to download and start an almost randomly chosen game obtained in some bundle, often a game which could linger in those large Steam libraties forever. Sadly, this game is not one of those. It promises to be a classic action-rpg with focus on combat, loot and character development. And although the interface is extremely big, the controls wonky and the dialogues rather uninteresting (and not voice-acted), I felt a certain urge to explare the outerspace world, kill those pesky aliens and find awesome loot. Sadly, the combat turned out to be very, very repetitive and boring, and - even worse - unbalanced. Since energy cells are not only the local currency but also the ammunition for your energy-powered weapons, I tried to rely on melee weapons to save ammo, but due to a lack of armour during the earliest stages of the game this didn't work out well. Since leveling proved to be extremely slow (and thus promising an endless grind-fest), I decided to quit this one, and look for another unknown game in my library.", "appid": "315260", "steamid": "profiles/76561198030080447", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "57", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1502712000.0}
