{"text": "Just my opinion, but I feel the game has poor game design. It feels like its padding its short play time (which is not a bad thing in my opion, shorter is better sometimes to me) with a bad check point system and an unneeded barrage of enemies... constantly. Die, then wait for loading, about 30 seconds.  With minimal loading (3-5 sec), or a better checkpoint system it would have worked and felt challenging but enjoyable. There's also the kind of weird upgrade system. Amazing graphics, love the art syle. The comic style art scene and loading screens are beautiful. Good sound design and atmosphere as well. If you like games that are punishing, then this is for you...i guess. Not a bad game, just not a game I'd recommned to anyone I know after playing it.", "appid": "98400", "steamid": "profiles/76561198035396704", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1416657600.0}
