{"text": "The game isn't a game and would hardly pass as a tech demo. The sounds are hideous, the models and their animations are clunky, and there's no way to find out how to do anything at all. No control legend, no explanation of the skill tree or points, nothing. Its a very obvious cash grab and poorly made at that, with no unique feature or mechanic or anything, really, to set it apart from any other dino game in the genre.  Uses assets from scam-game Mesozoica, possibly has some of the same devs, and ripping off audio from \"The Isle\" in its original trailer, is overall a bright red flag of \"likely a scam\" that's to be avoided.", "appid": "1215180", "steamid": "profiles/76561198118667774", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "24", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1591617600.0}
{"text": "The idea behind the game and the mechanics are inventive and inspired interesting playstyles and loadouts. That being said, the current game is rather broken, with gameplay favoring the survivors over the killers. Some of the killers are even outright unplayable in the current state of the game. There's also the fact that survivors have a tendency of rage quitting, meaning that as a killer if you're doing well, you end up being penalized because, again, you're doing well. There's no punishment for disconnecting from a match, so there's nothing to discourage players from doing so. Unless you have friends to play with, i wouldnt recommend picking this game up.", "appid": "381210", "steamid": "profiles/76561198002604918", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1535025600.0}
