{"text": "Grand Theft Auto IV is the perfect example of how NOT to make sandbox games. Its famous freedom of gameplay fails in pretty much everything it has to offer, and the reason for that â€“ the overwhelming boredom â€“ is the same for each and every activity. Firstly, the errand boy missions, or simply the filler missions, which make about 75% of the game (go, kill, shake the cops, repeat). Secondly, the monotonous side missions which are super easy and effortless and offer absolutely nothing that you might want or need. And thirdly, interacting with the environment, which is basically either ridiculously easy mini games (that's right, aim-assisted pool game, I'm talking about you) or just watching animations, shows or websites (which is nice aesthetically, but not gameplay-wise). The only things that work in this game, i.e. are entertaining, are shaking cops and big or humourous missionsâ€¦ which constitute only about 10% of the activities from the enormous palette Rockstar has prepared. To put it simply, the game as a whole is poor, even though it's big.", "appid": "12210", "steamid": "profiles/76561197997082432", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1592222400.0}
{"text": "The good:      > Artwork is awesome. The bad:      > Game mechanics are not great. The first reason is the design of the field. The perspective might work well for certain sports games (like basketball, soccer or football) but because you have to focus on your own positioning, your projectiles, your enemies projectiles and your enemy's position, you will go cross eyed very quick or die unjustly by running into an obstacle and not being able to course correct fast enough. A top to bottom perspective (like with a lot of tennis games) would've fared better.      > Secondly, the game is mostly dead online. When you find a match, you will be stuck in the loadscreen (at least from my experience).      > Thirdly  it doesn't have enough things to keep it interesting. No special items that spawn on the field to let you create diversions or give you a cheeky edge over opponents. Some characters feel more oppressive than others because having a higher ROF gives you an advantage over other characters. Its very poorly balanced.     > Finally the price is going to be a barrier to entry. There is not enough content to justify paying $15. I would recommend lowering the price to below $3.", "appid": "520670", "steamid": "profiles/76561198106323977", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1593086400.0}
