{"text": "PAYDAY2 is one of the best Co-op action shooters I have ever played. I fell in love with this game almost instantly and I always wanted to write a positive review. However, a lot of things have changed since the game's release. I found myself writing a negative review because of game developers. All this DLC craze is starting to get ridiculous - new content is introduced every month and 9 times out of 10 you need to pay for it. The biggest problem is that many DLCs are overpriced and useless. Overkill simply adds 1 or 2 weapons plus some masks and charges $5 for it. Needless to say, you will have a big advantage over other players if you purchase weapon DLCs and I find that unfair. The biggest dissapoint was introdused this week which is micro transactions. Overkill gave their word they will not implement anything like that, but I guess the money is far more important than game fans. Purchasing weapon skins in market gives you a tremendous advantage, because applying skins also increases your weapon stats. Simply put, Overkill is just milking this game like a cow in order to make the most profit possible. I must say I completely stopped playing it because of Pay-to-Win policy. All I wanted was to rob banks, but instead I'm being robbed by developers. The game - 9/10 Soundtrack - 10/10 EA.. oh.. I mean Overkill Studio - 0/10", "appid": "218620", "steamid": "profiles/76561198073947666", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1429963200.0}
