{"text": "SPOILERS AHEAD -TLDR AT BOTTOM- I've watched all of the terminator movies. I cringed in fear watching the first terminator crawling through the factory after Sarah Conner after it was blown in half by Kyle Reese. I watched as it cut its eye out when it was damaged. I watched it walk menacingly from the truck after it had exploded and had no flesh left. This game makes that Terminator look like a murder machine on steroids because the AI in this game is mentally handicapped beyond recognition. The AI in this game is subpar at the very least. I would crouch below half closed gates and watch \"ArTiFiCIaL InTeLLiGenCe\" machines sit there staring at me going \"wait they're crouched at a gate, how do we get to them!?\" and they just run around frantically before standing still and letting me just shoot them. I could hop on top of vehicles and machines just sit there looking at me like \"oh well, guess it's over Anakin they have the high ground\". What kind of blue blazing flapjack pancake fish stick bologne nonsense is that!? HOW can you CHEESE a Terminator's AI!? At the very least they should signal to other ranged Terminator machines to come shoot you. The AI was just as bad as Elder Scrolls Oblivion. You could shoot it a few times, hide around the corner, it would \"forget you're there\" then go back to pacing around, and repeat. OWWWWW WHO SHOT ME!? AHHHHH PAPA SKYNET SAVE ME!!! OHHHHH IT HURTS!!! Please what a joke. -_-   The machines should be striking fear into you not making you laugh as you sit there playing peak a boo shooting it in the butt every few moments watching it spin around frantically wondering how to \"reach you\". They should have made the T800 T 1000s + be able to break through walls and just grab your sorry butt and slam you around like a ragdoll for even showing your face and making you play super tactical and smart. The only thing they can do is strut around like Nutcracker dolls as they are trying to figure out pathing to get to you when you're literally right there, just around a corner, but they can't \"compute\" how to get there. -facepalm- On top of that I had issues with the game itself due to the game engine / graphics. Yes I exceed the minimum and recommended system specifications. Yes my graphics card is up to date. Yes my other settings are set up properly. To put it bluntly there is a GUIDE that tells you how to \"edit an ini file\" to \"make the system / game run smoother\". This is NOT Skyrim or Fallout 4! I should NOT have to edit INI files and do modding just to \"fix a game\" that doesn't even have some basic graphic settings in the options menu. Come on that's a bit ludicrous to say the least. It was so bad I finally just gave up and requested a refund. I'll go over some more things now for this game that are pros and cons. As I said these are my opinions. You might think they're funny, dumb, or whatever you think, but it's my honest opinion. That's how I review my games: HONESTLY. Decent voice acting Decent sound effects Decent music and ambient sounds Decent map and UI Decent control set up and can keybind change easily Sad pathetic excuse for an AI on a game. It's just as bad as Oblivion. Yes, it's that bad. You're forced to talent into lockpicking if you play on Hard mode+. If you want to be able to find ammo, trade supplies and other things at early game you HAVE to go into lockpicking. So if you wanted to sneak, do more damage or have a \"free choice\" to talent into other things think again. It's just 1 point, but that 1 point could be put into explosives to take down bigger enemies early on in the game. (Just a nuisance that bothers me personally. I hate feeling \"forced\" to have to pick something I may not want to.) No basic graphic controls / settings forcing you to edit game INI and other things to try to make it \"decent\". Don't get me wrong there are some graphic settings, but it's not in depth like most other modern games. This game released in 2019. Why am I missing graphic customization options on a game that recently released? Difficulty scaling is a bit drastic in my opinion. You go from normal to hard and hard mode is almost as bad as nightmare mode. Little to no ammo and if you try to \"sneak\" you can't due to map layout or excessive spider machines that run around like squirrels on crack forcing you to fight anyways, so...why is there a stealth option? Oh right you can just stand on a car anyways, so no big deal. Graphical issues in certain parts of the game. I experienced some flashing lights and flickering from gun muzzles that were not in sync with gun fire. I've never had this issue with other shooters especially recently released FPS games. Sometimes I wondered if I was at a Disco with a strobe light. Main character sounded a bit lackluster. Seemed like a lost puppy dog who was still a young boy and had a matching maturity to boot. Resistance fighter but sounds like he's either whining or uncertain most of the time. Kind of got annoying, but that's just my opinion. Character movement wasn't fully smooth. Seemed a bit clunky and laggy at times when running and moving. You can dash and \"slide\" but it's almost like my guy was going to go through the ground at times and then suddenly rubberband back up onto the surface. Was a weird experience. There is a \"scene\" in the game where you procreate with someone. \"Oh M G get over yourself!\" Let me finish... This \"person\" appears to be a young teenage girl. Sure it is an assumption, but it still seems kind of sus. The way they talk, look and act is that of a young teenage girl and not a lady of adequate age. Once again, it is an assumption, but still seems a bit fishy. I'm sure my opinion is unpopular since the game is voted \"very positive\", but I review in depth and I do nitpick many things. It's what I do. That being said the AI is very unbearable, boring and lacking to say the least. Other than that the graphic issues, lack of features for adjusting graphics included with the game and some other things I listed in the Con section are more than enough to make me shelf this game / request a refund. Playing it became so unbearable I couldn't even keep going. As a fan of the original Terminator movies and how the machines are portrayed this game does a poor job at displaying that. These aren't feared machines that punish 1 small mistake. These guys can't even figure out how to climb a car to kill you or what to do when you crouch inside a half opened garage door. If Skynet is this dumb...I think we're in trouble not because of the machines, but because the people who did the programming must have been pretty bad too. Makes me wonder what our toasters and microwaves might do when they malfunction in the future...", "appid": "954740", "steamid": "profiles/76561198216594040", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "21", "votes_funny": "8", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1604318400.0}
