{"text": "Sadly, I don't recommend this game: I loved Warband, but this is a disappointing follow up, along with a bunch of issues, bugs , including the performance (the system requirements are incorrect, 8 GB RAM is barely enough, don't even dream about running it with 6 GB). It is not worth it, especially at this price, unless you like to be a glorified beta tester for 49.99. 3/4 or at least half of the features presented in the pre-release devblogs are either missing, unfinished or just plain broken: - Missing: The ability to build and upgrade villages into castles, because TW realize their code is too bad for it. - Unfinished: The gang/criminal mechanic, it's not even rewarding either. You can just walk up to the gang leader without any resistance whatsoever, who is in a random building in a city (they also look like they just got timed out in dodgeball). You can't even play vigilante and attack the gang leader. - Plain broken: The perk tree, oh the perk tree. It's still not finished and is apparently just a placeholder, but it still sucks. 3/4 or half of the perks either don't work and if they do, the game will break them. I won't list them all, here is a website:  Wait until the game gets out of Early Access/gets better and gets a big sale (at least to 30 euros) and then consider buying it. Right now, it's a pathetic excuse of a sequel or even a game.", "appid": "261550", "steamid": "profiles/76561198077708670", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1589976000.0}
