{"text": "So, what happens if you take zombies and four unique characters in a post-apocalyptic world? Did you guess Walking Dead? No, its Left 4 Dead. This game wasn't that interesting to me. Its a very fun game in theory, but I lost interest to play another game after 5 or 6 servers I joined. The gameplay gets very repetative overtime. Kill zombies, move forward. Kill zombies, move forward. Kill zombies, move forward. You get my point? The characters, however, are very interesting and unique. Typical Valve of making their characters interesting. To be honest, I like the characters in the game more than the actual game itself. Do I recommend this game? For people wanting to kick undead ass and save society as we know it, I say a definite yes! For people who want to just play for a fun expirience...I don't know. That is up to you! For me, I'd say no.", "appid": "500", "steamid": "profiles/76561198409411459", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1538308800.0}
