{"text": "I seriously. Hated. This. Thing. I have no idea why this has great reviews unless they were mostly written by old men nostalgic for 1999. This thing is so dated. Do you like slurs? do you like macho men constantly threatening to murder each other out of some sort of affection? Also, do you like really ugly walking sims with strange controls and not being able to save unless you're in walking sim mode? Do you like weird boomeresque \"internet bad\" lines? Ok, how about most of the cast being clones. You cool with homophobia..? do you think people constantly swearing makes things cool and edgy? if so you'll love this pile of trash. It wants to be morally gray noir but in 1999. It's just. Bad. They also keep setting up thinkings like factions that never even matter because lmao they're all the same group they're just pretending so they can control everyone more effectively.. by making them kill each other? Also, you get to play the game twice if you want to complete it. Transmitter is incomprehensible a fair chunk of the time. Conversations eluding to conversations that were had off-screen. Until the big reveal! which is. So. So. Stupid. Basically the clones are clones of a dude with magical eyes who was also maybe a super-assassin except probably not the game bounces between the truth of that like a coin in the air. And that dude was murdered and someone stole his eyes. And stuffed them in their face. And now they're immortal. The 'silver' in the silver case refers to his eyes. This is revealed at the end of Transmitter, because it's just so dumb that they had to hide it behind layers and layers of other stuff like they're ashamed of it. Or like cults that hide their strangest ideas from the mainstream because if you heard it, to begin with, you'd nope out before getting too invested. But the sunk-time fallacy works in their favor. Placebo the second arc is more boring but more straight forward. Story still bad. This isn't clever. This isn't funny. This is nonsense. 21-year-old nonsense. I am so glad I didn't get the sequel when it was on sale. Because I don't want to know how stupid that one gets. I'd have quit early on if I wasn't a completionist and if I could have refunded it, but I'd had it sitting around a while. The soundtrack is.. okish? You know the Danganronpa composer? He did the one for this and you can hear some of the motifs he likes to use. That and. Some character art is ok-ish..? are like the only nice things I can say about this. Mess.  Thanks I Hate it.", "appid": "476650", "steamid": "profiles/76561198062749545", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "11", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1596456000.0}
