{"text": "I loved the original Ultima Underworld and was quite happy when I discovered that some people involved with that old gem were working on a sequel of sorts. Likely not an official sequel because licensing is a nightmare with both EA and Garriott holding some of the rights. Regardless, I was looking very forward to this but had almost forgotten about it as it is about 2.5 years overdue from the originally projected release. After all that extra time, surely those experienced developers had created a marvelous game. What could possibly go wrong? Oh, whatever happened in those 3.5 years of development? Because this title has turned out to be a total desaster. It's not even fit for beta. Poor performance, horrible UI, not much of a story and a plethora of bugs and glitches. As far as quality standards are concerned it reminds me of Shroud of the Avatar but, unbelievably, this is even worse. Right, couldn't really believe such a thing to be possible, either. Is there a curse on games inspired by Ultima titles? Arx Fatalis and Xultima did pretty good, so more likely a curse on former game developer luminaries. Maybe in a year or two this might have been in a reasonably playable state, but at this time I very much doubt this will ever get properly fixed, unless it gets the community patch treatment. Though I am not really sure it would be worth the effort to even try. Best forgotten. Mental note: stay away from \"spiritual successors\" of old games.", "appid": "692840", "steamid": "profiles/76561197974007233", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "24", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1542456000.0}
