{"text": "Personally, a few years ago, I would have said this game was decent, and it was! Shooting cops (in a video game) is fun, and the gun customisation is great, along with the mask customisation, you get a good mixture of eras of weaponry, and the missions were decently designed. I enjoy playing it from time to time, preferably with friends, because playing it alone is really boring. It got very, very repetitive, but this game was once decent, imagine that? But now? Oh god no. Don't buy this. It used to be around a 6/10, but now it's a solid 3/10. Mainly due to the overwhelming amount of paid DLC, paid DLC, that - might I add - is overpriced. There is 50+ DLCS IN THIS GAME, AND THERE WILL BE MORE. Currently, if you wanted to buy this game with all the DLC, you can either buy the Legacy Edition, or you can pay $200+ FOR IT ALL INDIVIDUALLY. This is reaching EA levels of stupid, here!! Now, on to the controversy: So, this game used to have an Ultimate Edition, because the company PROMISED they would not implement more DLCs, that was all they were putting into the game. Recently, they renamed the Ultimate Edition to the \"Legacy Edition\", I believe, and announced they would continue adding paid DLCs. A thing which they promised they wouldn't do, and this new \"Legacy Edition\" will only include the DLCs released BEFORE this new DLC came out, \"The Silk Road\". So basically what they've done is this, they've scammed their previous customers, lied to us, and thought we were stupid. Don't buy this game, wait until someone releases a version that has all the DLC on P!rate Bay, don't even get it on a key-reseller, you'll regret buying this game. Granted, it's fun, and shooting cops (in video games) is fun, but it gets repetitive REAL quick, and do you really want to support a company as â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ as Starbreeze and Overkill? I really don't think I want to. Nice try guys, but I'm not dumb, I'm not buying into your â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥. How ironic that a game about robbing and killing, is just there to rob your money from you. This game is a heist of your money, and is an insult to PAYDAY: The Heist. I'm sorry Payday, that you had to have such a â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ sequel.", "appid": "218620", "steamid": "profiles/76561198057868880", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1401883200.0}
