{"text": "Hmmmm this game looks fun, is fun. The downfall is it made my PC very hot and i could not play past 15 minutes without my computer shutting itself off due to the heat, i tried 4 times.. -.- and mind you, my computer can easily handle the specs on this game. I dont know what it is about it. I can run Tom clancy wildlands on high no problem. Sadly had to get a refund. I wont play this when it makes my pc freak out.", "appid": "365590", "steamid": "profiles/76561198090750115", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1494072000.0}
{"text": "This game is slowly dieing and it produces the smallest and most sadest updates I have ever seen, and yet they dont actually work , if anything cause more bugs. It also dosent help when there is a very over-hyped community from a click-baiting youtuber that trys to show off game changing events that the developer trys to back up, but yet they never come out. Then this pushes some fanboy whiteknights of this youtuber to have to come out a leak it to the public. Another thing about the developers is that they have been working on this project for over 2 years now (asuming) and yet a game thats been in an alpha for 2 months can get more support and feedback then this game. Matter of fact I think modders put more game fixes then the devs do but then the modding community in this game sucks and 90% of the time the mod brakes more â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ then what its fixes so it becomes worthless. Now I do enjoy this game but its a risky price to pay for if you decide to buy this pothetic thing for a game. Sadly I am addicted to this game. PS, sorry if I had any spelling errors or grammer errors I guess i am handecapped when it comes to spelling. Ok so it has been some time from the last time i have played this game, and the game seems to be improving, but improving in the way that it is slowly dropping in the number of players, content/updates, and less public attention. The majority of the players that still attempt to enjoy this game dont even play the way the hole game is made to do. The Isle is a game where you are to survive as playable dinosaurus in a prehistoric world, not a game to have rules in servers to wear people are told how to play the game. Server owners and admins are the biggest downfall to this game. If the where just  open servers then most of the game would be to survive and hunt, but now server hosts like to add rules like No KOS, Only Chill/No Kill which make zero sense( dont carnivores need to eat to survive). The rules then end up starting harrasment between people on if they break the rules or not. In the end the rules add more negativity in this game then without them ( I mean come on now, who wants others to controll how you play). Another problem is people do stick to a more realistic style of the game, meaning they dont play the game on how it was ment to be played. Herbivores and Carnivores are like WWE in this â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ anymore cause all they do is tag team on discord to ruin the fun for others. And if its not herby kos it revenge killing ( or over exesive killing) meaning you are huntng way more then you need, but hunting is on you and tbh i am not trying to control how you play, I am just stating on how this game is played by others. Not to forget if you have any questions let me know in the comments dont shy and let me know how you think The Isle is going to be in the future or if you need any questions feel free to ask cause if I dont even respond i bet someone else will. I have over 2500 hours on my accounts in total on this game and I can tell you a thing or 2.", "appid": "376210", "steamid": "profiles/76561198170936262", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1464091200.0}
{"text": "I don't know why this game has such high ratings. The story is uninteresting, character development is cliche. The ending of the game does not pay off, considering the leadup to the end of the game is essentially half of the game itself. Voice acting is just odd, and I'm pretty sure they just used the whole \"reading a bedtime story\" as a cover up. The only thing this game has going for it is the look itself (other than the NPCs). Its actually quite pretty.  There are some segments where it seems like you can't make it unless its pixel perfect.  Buy this game for the gameplay, and mute all sounds.", "appid": "278360", "steamid": "profiles/76561198204423829", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1543665600.0}
