{"text": "Tribal Wars is a game that has been out for a long time, 2003 to be exact. Recently brought to Steam to increase the population of players and to get more 'seen' by those who like playing games like these. It's a game where you have to upgrade your town and it's level and spend a lot of resources, time and effort to grow. Growing is quite easy in the beginning but once your resources run out, you need to wait. Every single time you upgrade your buildings you need to wait.. Wait and wait. The higher the level the longer you will have to wait. This, can be solved by buying premium and in-game packs/items which not also gain you finish the buildings quicker but also the resources, troops and others like other games related to Tribal Wars. There are a lot of reviews going on, not only on Steam but take 5 minutes of your life searching on Google 'Tribal Wars Reviews' and you will gain knowledge about the whole game instantly about people talking about grinding, spending a lot of time and a huge amount of money to be in the possible top 10 ranks in Tribal Wars. The game still has potential, but overall, in the beginning there are just so many options and features that it makes you very confused. Me and some others tried playing this game this week and we just don't actually know what to do, no well-written, detailed and easy to understand guides whatsoever. You simply upgrade here and there and you have to find everything out yourself. Ofcourse, there is Youtube but having a tutorial/guide which is easy to understand is a must have which Tribal Wars don't have unless you search everything up yourself. Another thing is the Pay2Win.. So many games related to Tribal Wars where you have to upgrade buildings, make troops to destroy other towns and whatever are having a big Pay2Win vibe and Tribal Wars is having this as well. If you are going to play Tribal Wars right now, the only thing i can say 'Best of luck'. You will compete with players that already spend a lot of time and money into the game and the only way to get better, higher power etcetera is by spending money. If you want to play without spending money, you will still be far away from the top 100. When spending money, i suggest waiting till a new server opens and spend money instantly. The game looks nice, unique in a way but the overall gameplay is just not it. Again, find reviews on Google about Tribal Wars or feel free to test it out yourself since it's a Free2Play game. But i personally don't recommend it due the Pay2Win vibe, no clear and well-written instructions and the poor optimization.", "appid": "675690", "steamid": "profiles/76561198056046060", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1605614400.0}
