{"text": "After all the hours i've put in this game, unfortunately i still can't recommend it to anyone.  Since day one, the game has that one issue: It keeps crashing on launch or it randomly crashes between autosaves.  A few patches back this was partially solved by changing a line inside a txt file. With the latest patch though the crash issues have returned once more making the game completely unplayable. Possible solutions on community are not really solving the problem.  They might work for a while but few restarts later the game for whatever reason will start crashing again. The only thing you can do after is a complete reinstall, then again change stuff in the directory and hope for a miracle. On the other hand and if you feel lucky enough, leaving the game to open without clicking anywhere on screen or alt-tab (so no hang error will occur) might allow the game to launch/load after 5+(!) minutes of waiting.  I am just so disappointed to see the same thing happening since its release. I am not even interested in the new expansion coming out anymore, which looks so damn good!  Why would i even get it if the base game will not work properly or not work at all.  Sorry paradox but this is trully the worst game release you ever did.", "appid": "859580", "steamid": "profiles/76561198028556241", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "290", "votes_funny": "47", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1584619200.0}
{"text": "This game is painful to finish. Maps are creepy being much better than the other fan-made products Redemption and Recurring Evil but they are extremely bugged. They are very large and have many areas that look like geometric figures and you get stuck often in objects having to resort to auto-save. AND the monsters are getting lost on the map very often having to search for them all the time, and the compass does not help you too much because of the map being large. AND there are times when you have to figure out yourself the right way to go because the game does not give you too many checkpoints and beleive me its a pain to find the ways especially in the first two levels. AND there are also some confusing puzzles that makes you to resort to youtube to proceed further, like for example one being to distroy a wall to get an entrance to a cave, an idea that will less likely pop into your mind. The game has also random freezes and it crashes with error message. This is my experience with this game and I am sharing it with you so that you know on what you will spend your money. In my opinion the developers and game tester did not put a drop of passion and heart in this game and they built it in a hurry just for the $.", "appid": "39560", "steamid": "profiles/76561198201820005", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1565870400.0}
