{"text": "-If you expect a game where you feel like you are Batman? Nope, this is not it.  -You expect a game where DC lore is followed â€“even slightly? Nope, definitely not.  -You want a decent story where your choices actually matter? Hell, you wish.  This game is written so poorly that during most of your gameplay, you will want to skip the conversations... well, the combat also sucks so youâ€™ll want to skip that too. You can ignore literally 90% of the QTEs and you WILL survive.  The story makes no sense. No sense at all.  This Batman game is an insult to all Batmans ever written.  Catwoman   I have been pushing her away ever since the first game, and still the game forces me to romance her. You think you have an option? No. You HAVE to romance her.  Oh, but hey we have some well-known figures from the DC universe like Riddler, Harley Quinn or Bane so we can write anything we want just using their name. THATâ€™S NOT HOW IT WORKS. None of these characters including Alfred, Bruce and Gordon feel like they are believable. This whole game feels like just another teenage drama. And you are dating Joker. Can you imagine Batman defying law and justice   Yeah, me neither. Thank you Telltale, with your writing I hate most of the DC characters now. Hereâ€™s an example of how your choices matter: Thereâ€™s this girl Tiffany, whiny daughter of Lucius who always blames you for everything bad happens to her. I picked the option to kick her out of my office when given the chance, but I saw some people havenâ€™t   Well, I didnâ€™t, obviously. In the end, it didnâ€™t matter because she came to the manor to HELP ME and told Bruce â€œI value your opinion.â€ right after the game told me she felt alienated in the previous episode. Do I need to say that I scolded, mocked or even tried not to save her when she was in danger? Why do you even value my opinion if I was so awful to you? Because it doesnâ€™t matter. None of your choices matter.   No matter what they pull the same â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥.  This game is a waste of time.  How the heck   Was that on the news or something, because it definitely feels like it.  Also Iâ€™m utterly sorry to say this but â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ you   He sides with everyone BUT Bruce.  You want to play a good Telltale game? Play something else.  +Pros to whoever is the voice actor of Joker, damn they have wasted his talent on this crappy character in this crappy game.", "appid": "675260", "steamid": "profiles/76561198089005817", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "39", "votes_funny": "13", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1574856000.0}
