{"text": "I was hoping for Risen of the wild instead i got insane logic and hand holding. Hey your shipwrecked a mile from your Village....How is this a thing? Especially when you say a certain race is born on the sea which i happened to pick? Hey can i go swim in the water? nope there's an invisible wall saving you from   a survival game. Hold button gather wood, uh where's my axe? You don't need an Axe you just get wood from it cause that's how things work.  Oh hey you know how you went through the tutorial and the game told you if the gray bar is drained you just get knocked down? Well the actual game didn't get the memo. fought bandits, got knocked down with half hp instantly captured, Should just be dead, but no i'm drop in a room with no doors, a weapon and armor. No one is that stupid to leave the prisoner in the cell with the door open and leave a weapon with them, Not even storm troopers.       So you equip the mace try to escape i get spotted thinking ok they're definitely gonna kill me this time.....Get knocked down captured and put in the same room again with the mace the clothes and no door...Dark Souls would have had the decency to kill my dumb ass. this game goes \"aww did you fall down and go boom? here have this mace and clothes and give it another go champ\" You remember how you learned in the tutorial you need a rune to cast magic and spark for a fireball? yeah the praying mantis the size of a cow doesn't need runes to shoot lightning balls at you and can shoot them endlessly. plus it's pretty close to the main gate near the beach that i can't drown or swim in. Side note you could only afford to voice act the first half of sentences? I can't tell if this is lazy, stupid,  incompetent, or all the above. This game just makes me think \"I don't know how to script or code that well nor draw that great but i know i could do better it would probably be an RPGmaker game but it still be better\"", "appid": "794260", "steamid": "profiles/76561198067655146", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1553601600.0}
