{"text": "Pretty sure this is the first \"Review\" I have ever done. I`m doing it because this game has so many positive reviews and honestly its not good. To be fair i think the one single thing decent about this game is the story witch id rate not a single point above a 5. Combat is awful, hell just walking feels awful. Its made by capcom and its was released in 2012 so there are no excuses. This was my first RE game and I hope if i try another they will be better.  I`m leaving it at just this because i don`t want to list off everything in the game its simply not good and not at all worth $30. If you can find this for around $5 id say its worth it. BTW this is not a horror game... At all.", "appid": "222480", "steamid": "profiles/76561198342188953", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1557489600.0}
{"text": "Final boss is bugged... yeah, ground all the way to him and he disappeared as soon as my mage buddy hit him with an ice attack.  It is a fun game, but it doesn't hit it's potential.  It has no endless mode, which is what alot of rogue-like players enjoy about the genre.   Placing stats onto your character between each level is enjoyable, and the game is fun.  However it seems incomplete.   For the price, a 2d game like this should have alot more content, alot more replayability and a lot more functionality.   I could barely believe that the final boss glitched out, that is a big deal.", "appid": "323220", "steamid": "profiles/76561198143355773", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "12", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1525521600.0}
