{"text": "I've got this game for free. And I regret it a bit. The first thing is, that this game has a really poor performance for that little thing what they call 'graphics'. Sometimes this game drops under the 60FPS and this is really eye cancer on a 144Hz monitor. But, what about the gameplay? The gameplay is boring, and I didn't play the first game. But I heard from some friends, that the first game does make more fun than this. But as I can tell, this is good game to talk and play with your friends. But I think you could also play the first game and would have a lot more fun. Then I see, this game has ingame credits, which you can buy with real money. I hate this transactions and as I could see, they are for skins. SKINS. I can't understand why you should buy these, but hey, you get 4000 of these diamonds at the beginning! Now you can buy 2 or 3 skins and you can also open cases! Great thing. No, not really. If I would have paid for this, it would be a shame for me. I think you should better play the first game, really. But for those of you, that have fun with this game, have fun. I can't have it and I didn't play it for an hour. It is just eye cancer with fps below the 60FPS and I think my rig should hold this.", "appid": "236110", "steamid": "profiles/76561198077079690", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1444305600.0}
