{"text": "Edit: 10/30/19 I do have feelings for Injustice 2 as the first game been one of my favorites for a long time. However I will unfortunately have to not recommend this to anyone. Yeah, I can play it locally but I2 hasn't been properly advertised before its release on PC, which is why there aren't as much players on PC compared to PS4 or Xbox. It should have been released on all platforms simultaneously. This game has been ported poorly as some functions require a controller or using the keyboard, and you can't increase your FPS above 60 (I don't know, maybe its for competitive issues). Graphics look very good on the highest settings and gameplay hasn't really changed from Injustice 1 which is good and bad at the same time. I kinda expected more from this sequel. The story in Injustice 2 is perfect, and I like how you can choose characters before the fight. But unfortunately the cutscenes are pre-rendered and I'm not a big fan of that at all. Customization in I2 is endless as you can select a wide variety of cosmetic and stat-changing items for your characters. But I do have to say that most of these items are easily unlockable through the predatory loot box system. The good thing is it's too late to call it pay-to-win because there's not enough players to play with each other. Overall, it is statistically a good game but there aren't enough players to keep the game up and running. I guarantee Warner Bros will not be making an Injustice sequel. If you want to get it, definitely not worth its default price and best to get it on a sale. Good luck finding an online match.", "appid": "627270", "steamid": "profiles/76561198333764689", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1511611200.0}
