{"text": "I bought the 'game' after watching people play it. Most people chose the wrong options which I thought was hilarious. So I gave it a go, for the laugh of it. And it didn't dissapoint.. On that point, at least. After I started I got the feeling like they try a little too hard to be serious, but then you get to choose from all those hilarious, but wrong options. And it's hard to take it seriously after that.  Don't get me wrong, it sure is fun to watch all those clips of people going mental on someone or saying something absurdly idiotic or just the bad acting of it. But this wasn't meant to be a comedy netflix show. A little humor here or there is fine, I think, but this is just off putting.  In the 10 chapters, there were 3 times when Richard said some actual good advise. So if you want to buy this for the dating advice, it would be better if you looked elsewhere. If you want a good laugh tho, then I think you should get it. Then again, you can just easily watch it on youtube and save the 10 euros.  In conclusion, they made a game/video about dating advice, but it's all over the place. Already after the intro you have a hard time takeing it seriously. Is it trying to be some sort of comedy or some legit relationship advice thing? Pick one or the other..  And I want to also point out that some of the achivements appear to be bugged. Some people had issues with some not popping up. For me, the last one got bugged and I didn't get it. Thanks for that.. And btw, what is up with those people just standing there behind Richard in those 'advice' clips..?", "appid": "863570", "steamid": "profiles/76561197988942672", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1597924800.0}
