{"text": "Even with 10 hours of gameplay it wouldn't be hard to realize why I'm not recommending this game, the main reason is already at the publisher, it's Gameforge that ALONE is enough to showcase how much of a suffering this game is and Gameforge is the solo reason this game is dying..litterally there were times I saw the game only having about 73 players at certain times and that's 50% afk people because for some â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ reason it's rare for me to see a moving person but anyways. If you ever played a game published by Gameforge you will probably know it...if EA is a cashgrab then boi this is a universal heist operation and the problem is at this point I would've been happy if it was also grind to win too not even pay to win, your grind will mean nothing or the money you spend will mean anything because of how overpriced this game is, if you grind your life out of it and finnaly decide upgrade your weapon that took you a 100+ hours and your sanity and if you still have some braincells remaining don't worry upgrading will probably take away the rest of them because even gods luck won't even gonna help this monster, the chance for your upgrade to success is lower then a flying pig coming from Andromeda to kill you with the smallest pistol ever...I mean even that could be possible by the time you manage to upgrade.. And the market prices are probably the craziest thing ever...because of the universal IQ of Gameforge they managed to ruin them by certain events etc which caused the prices to be unimaginabely high and the fact they are bringing back costumes that were supposed to be rare as direct purchase also ruined it too just so they could add a few bucks to their money pool Oh and don't even think \"Oh I can just farm\" if you're going for an expensive costume like Holy Seat or a wing like Golden Demon Wings there is no way you can farm them because there isn't a way to farm DZ fairly anymore it's only farming ECs or brooches and selling them which you would be lucky if people will be able to afford them they even reduced the money drop rates of certain places so your only way would probably be farming even more EC by farming AoV- oh wait the drop chances for a gear is also low...well if you get one and dismantle- Nwm you won't probably get an EC well maybe you get an EC oh wait they only sell for like 17m good luck getting a 1b costume  In general maybe you will have some fun from the playstyle etc until you reach about lvl 60 then you need to get AoV gear but don't even think about joining randoms no one will accept anyone without an AoV gear TO THE ONE PLACE WHERE THEY CAN GET AOV GEAR..well maybe try to find some people that will help you...the problem is you need a team to improve, you can't improve solo but you can't also get in a team with randoms so after that it's just pure grind and fraustration..farming for AoV gear and then upgrading that gear to a state where you will be at least minium allowed to HH which will already gonna waste all your money and resources and then you farm HH then get that set and waste your ECs and resources and money on them as well and then get a flexor for them and farm even more to even be able to apply that flexor, you will also need to buy brooches which won't be a problem during the current event because everyone who can breathe can easily get the supposed to be rare Assassin brooches now...welcome to Soulworker and enjoy your stay!", "appid": "630100", "steamid": "profiles/76561198242565282", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1548244800.0}
