{"text": "First of all, a really nice game on its own, really love the massive jump from the original to this one But there's one thing that bothers me and genuinely makes this game unplayable for me: At some point the levels start getting actively nauseous, meaning your viewing distance gets significantly decreased and after a certain distance the level zooms away from you, letting everything around you appear rooted in the void And when you move the effect moves with you, meaning the level is basically in constant motion This also affects the way you perceive the enemies since you have no real context for distance And I only became actively aware of that effect when I was already severely nauseous (and I rarely get motion sick or anything similar, not even related to moving images but this is something extreme) So, if any developers see this, please add at least an option to disable the \"zooming\" as I call it", "appid": "690040", "steamid": "profiles/76561198202988303", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1595419200.0}
